630	7261167	Sr. UX Designer 	New York, New York	Our client is a leading media/publishing organization with 4 active business units and about 150 employees.<br />\n<br />\nThey are currently seeking a <strong>Senior UI/UX Designer</strong> to join their digital product team in their Manhattan headquarter office. This role reports directly to the Director of UX and works closely with Product Managers and Engineers to best support and execute the various product design needs. The Sr. UI/UX Designer will also be responsible for clearly communicating and annotating all products for development. Join a strong product team as the brand undergoes a full digital overhaul!<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experienced with responsive design, mobile web and responsive/adaptive email design</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Produce sketches, wireframes, lo/hi fidelity prototypes, UI kits, and visual design comps </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Help define workflows and UX/UI requirements per project (create personas as needed, conduct interviews, research, iterate etc.)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Develop and manage all research and user testing initiatives</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Iterate design changes, contribute to our style guide and implement design principles across our products</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Evangelize experience design throughout the organization</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Annotate all work to communicate clear and concise interaction(s) with engineers</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Interpret analytics to accurately design experiences according to our user’s needs</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong>Qualifications:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent work experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">4-7 years’ experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Highly creative, detail-oriented, passionate about delivering the best user experience possible</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Portfolio demonstrating solid UX, UI and Visual Design skills</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Understanding of interactive design principles, UX/UI design, best practices and usability</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite and Axure  </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Familiarity with working with engineers</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Rich media advertising experience a plus</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work independently and juggle multiple UX projects at a time</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience working in an agile development environment a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong>Notes:</strong>\n\n<ul>