n for software applications running in browsers<br />\n- Bachelor’s degree (Master’s preferred) in HCI, Cognitive Psychology, Industrial Design, Computer Science, Engineering Psychology, or a related field<br />\n- Demonstrated experience conducting user-centered design projects<br />\n- Proven ability to generate designs from the conceptual level through to production detailing<br />\n- Demonstrated experience developing and communicating User Experience design guidelines, templates, and standards<br />\n- Strong familiarity with design principles for rich, interactive visualizations<br />\n- Proven effectiveness working in cross-functional teams that include product management, engineering, marketing, and other User Experience professionals<br />\n- Demonstrated proficiency with prototyping tools such as Fireworks, Photoshop, Flash, Visio, Axure, etc.<br />\n- Familiarity with summative user research techniques<br />\n- Excellent written and verbal skills	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.167198	2016-06-01 00:00:08.168327	Informatica	\N	t	\N
