797	7593599	Senior Product Designer	New York, New York	<div>Our client is a 6 year old, 64-person B2B software company located in NoHo. With exceptional ratings on Glassdoor, and a beautiful office, they work on software which is revolutionizing wholesale, (anything prior to retailers). This includes manufacturers and distributors which span across numerous industries.</div>\n\n<div>As a Senior Product Designer, you’ll design and shape user-centric products and experiences. Working on the same team as product managers, UX designers, and developers, your simple and powerful interface designs will be an integral part of how every product reaches every shelf worldwide.</div>\n\n<div>Our Clients mission is to help manufacturers & distributors grow their business by making it easy for their customers to order the right products from them in-person and online. The software they build provides their customers with a commerce platform that replaces the antiquated paper-and-clipboard-based systems used by brands and their salespeople, allowing for more products to reach more retailers with less cost, at greater speed and with less environmental impact.</div>\n\n<div><strong><strong> </strong></strong></div>\n\n<div><strong>The Problems You&#39;ll Solve</strong></div>\n\n<div>Designers collaborate to solve difficult problems together to ensure the initial and ongoing success of our client&#39;s customers. Some of the biggest challenges their designer teammates are solving right now are:</div>\n\n<div><strong><strong> </strong></strong></div>\n\n<div><strong>- Developing a Visual Language</strong></div>\n\n<div>Our client was initially built to help small brands sell their products at trade-shows, but has been growing ever since to adapt to the needs of international brands and distributors. As they continue to grow, having a consistent visual language across our products is key to helping unify the experience for our customers. Working with the design team, you’ll develop gui