CATIONS</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proven track record of strategic thought leadership</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">10+ years of UX experience, 7+ years in a leadership role, preferably within finance or investment banking</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Deep understanding of product development</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong understand of Front-End technologies (e.g., HTML, Javascript, CSS, Flash, Flex)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Hands on expertise with Use case development, prototyping, storyboarding, mock-ups</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proven ability to manage long-term, complex engagements with multiple project tracks and teams</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong analytical, planning and project management skills</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proven ability to make informed decisions in complex and judgmental areas</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">The ability to thrive in a collaborative environment</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong people leadership skills including demonstrated success developing others as well as a track record of getting results in partnership with others</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong communication skills and the ability to engage and inspire others</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong executive presence and ability to engage, interact and influence</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience leading multiple large projects simultaneously</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience must include understanding of and utilization of analysis of user interface research, user experience and market data</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div> <br />\n<strong>Series 7 licensing must be attained within 12 months of start date</strong></div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.396137	2016-06-01 00:00:08.29323	Edward Jones	In-house	t	UX Design, Product Design, Research
644	6227507	Lead UX Designer	Los Angles, CA	Our client was established in 2006 by entrepreneurial gamers who believe that player-focused game development can result in great games. Their highest played game gets over 67 million plays every month. <br />\n<br />\nSeeking humble but ambitious, razor-sharp professionals who can teach us a thing or two. We promise to return the favor. Like us, you take play seriously; you’re passionate about games. We embrace those who see things differently, aren’t afraid to experiment, and who have a healthy disregard for constraints.<br />\n<br />\nThat’s where you come in.<br />\n<br />\nAs a Lead User Experience Designer, for Riot Games, you’ll work closely with researchers, interdisciplinary teams and other stakeholders to understand our game players and build top-notch user experiences handcrafted to meet their needs. You’ll help shape the UX direction of end-to-end player solutions and find opportunities for further research, improvement and innovation. You’ll also lead a team to define and implement design standards that enable us to create a consistent, quality experience for players across every aspect of *, from the website to the client and everything in between.<br />\n<br />\n<u><strong>YOU ARE:</strong></u>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">User experienced: you know core user experience design principles better than you know your own mom, and you’re an expert at the UX tools in your toolbox</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Visionary thought leader, and a domain expert</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Creatively collaborative: you prefer agile to waterfall any day of the week, and your best work comes from a place of collaboration and teamwork; you play nice with others and know that quality results come from strong communication throughout the design process</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Design independent: you’re comfortable with some degree of ambiguity, and you confidently hit your stride in even the fastest of fast-paced development environments; your brainstorms make other brainstorms look like headsprinkles or nogginfoggies, and you find fresh solutions where others fall victim to ideological dry spells</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Data-driven: You use quantitative analytics and user research to inform your UX designs solutions (pre and post launch), and you know how to articulate ideas that have logic and data to support them</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A web technophile: you understand the technologies involved in creating great web experiences and your designs account for their inherent strengths and limitations</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Player-focused: you love games and game culture; you use your experiences as a gamer along with your knowledge of user-centered design to achieve both player and business goals, and have stories of “a-ha” moments you had while talking with players</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>YOU WILL:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Help lead the UX design process within cross-functional teams to solve business and player problems</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Educate and evangelize the importance of human factors, player feedback and data-driven decision making in end-to-end user experience design</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with stakeholders and teammates to gather, understand and codify requirements for various projects</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Create interface wireframes and user flows, ensuring iterative feedback is incorporated throughout the development process</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with your UX teammates to define and maintain interaction pattern libraries we can  share with the rest of team </li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Active (1)	2016-05-26 19:30:28.379974	2017-03-30 16:00:11.444326	Riot Games	In-house	t	\N
