646	5964155	Senior Interaction Designer	New York, New York	<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; text-align: center;">Senior Interaction Designer<br />\n<em>Work with the best of the best on products used worldwide!</em><br />\n </div>\n<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;">Overview:<br />\nOur client, a global financial technology and media company offering state of the art offices and a best in class UX design model is adding 2-3 Senior Interaction Designers to their team of innovators who are committed to creating valuable and meaningful user experiences for their customers. You will transform complex data and work processes into products that are indispensable to users.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span style="line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">The role:</span><br />\n<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;">The Senior Interaction Designer will be responsible for </span>designing complex transactional systems with the goal of making intuitive and valuable products. Interaction Designers at our client are excellent analytical and conceptual thinkers that translate user needs, business objectives and technology capabilities into innovative design.<br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;" />\n<br />\nDiving deeper:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Senior Interaction Designers are involved in all aspects of the design process from context-based research to storyboarding and presenting to internal clients. Success depends on close collaboration and partnerships with end-users and subject matter experts, as well as product and technology counterparts. This position will take ownership of a domain to envision and craft conceptual frameworks, interaction design and the overall user experience of new products and major enhancements.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Interaction Designers at our client form a core team that is responsible for the highest impact business and platform products. In addition, this team provides design stewardship and governance through a customized UI toolkit that specifies interactions at a very granular level. Interaction Designers create and maintain standards for this toolkit as well as recommended design patterns for their technology team. Through collaboration with the technology and product teams, designers are able to test solutions in real-time and instantaneously deliver software to customers.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">This position is for a thoughtful designer with a passion for making complex data and workflow problems simpler. This individual thrives in a highly collaborative and cross-disciplinary team environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nQualifications:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Undergraduate or Graduate Degree in HCI, Interaction Design, Information Architecture, Visual Communication, or any design-related field.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5 + years of experience designing transactional or highly interactive user interfaces.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in several of the following: designing complex user workflows, decision-support systems, large dataset visualizations and framework-level interactions, information architecture, graphic/visual design, usability research/analysis.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Track record of applying common User-Centered Design practices and tools to solve tough design problems.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Knowledge of the software development lifecycle and its varying methodologies</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in project management a plus.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience on institutional finance projects involving transactional interfaces is a huge plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nPortfolio:<br />\nOur client would ideally like to see artifacts from across the project lifecycle. Your representative projects may include, but should not be limited to: research, personas, sketches, site maps, task flows, wireframes, storyboards, etc. They are, however, most interested in seeing detailed wireframes (preferably a deck) illustrating a step-by-step user workflow for complex transactional interfaces. An ideal project to showcase for us would have an intricate user interface that you can use to explain your detailed design decisions. Please include two (2) projects where you can give them a "deep-dive" into your design process.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	On Hold	2016-05-26 19:30:28.390539	2016-06-01 00:00:08.243734	Bloomberg	\N	t	\N
632	7515640	UX Designer	New York, NY	<div>We are looking for a UX designer who will settle for nothing less than an environment that equally emphasizes killer UCD work and personal growth and development. You’ll be a hands-on contributor to user research, concepting, client workshops, interaction design, user journeys, personas, site maps, wireframes, prototyping and testing and grow your skills to position you to eventually become a great UX Lead.</div>\n\n<div>You’ll be a part of a passionate product design team within a culture that values human-insights-lead strategy and client empathy over big surprise reveals. You’ll work seamlessly with UX Leads, content strategists, other UX designers, visual designers, product managers, developers and clients on enterprise-level products and apps that impact business, win awards and leave every user feeling loved.</div>\n\n<div>You’ll have impact. You’ll have ownership. And one more thing—you&#39;ll enjoy it.</div>\n\n<h3>Key Responsibilities:</h3>\n\n<div>• Develop innovative user-focused experiences that balance clients’ business objectives, user’s needs and technical complexity.</div>\n\n<div>• Own the quality and completion of all UX deliverables on projects.</div>\n\n<div>• Partner with a UX Lead to define the vision and prioritize requirements and functional needs.</div>\n\n<div>• Contribute to client and internal presentations with the goal of owning and leading them.</div>\n\n<div>• Collaborate with the project team to define and execute correct research and testing processes.</div>\n\n<div>• Share your UX knowledge and champion UX and UCD principles throughout the company.</div>\n\n<h3>Skills/Qualifications:</h3>\n\n<div>• Has 3+ years of experience in the field of UX Design or product development, working with large-scale and complex digital experiences or applications.</div>\n\n<div>• Is a great communicator; you know how to break down complex concepts, approaches and designs into simple explanations that put clients and team members at ease.</div>\n\n<div>• Has a modern and clean design aesthetic; your wireframes reflect simplicity, usability and consistency.</div>\n\n<div>• Has a curious mind; you listen well and observe, analyze, question, synthesize and conceptualize.</div>\n\n<div>• Is an entrepreneur at heart; takes initiative, never content with your skill level and continually looks to do more with less.</div>\n\n<div>• Is an optimist; always finding creative ways &#39;we can do&#39; instead of thinking about what &#39;we can&#39;t do&#39;.</div>\n\n<div>• Understands that harmony between design and technology is essential to create exceptional and meaningful work.</div>\n\n<div>• Thrives in a work environment where there is constant cross-collaboration between design, user experience, strategy, product and technology.</div>\n\n<div>• Lives for the craft of design and has a relentless focus on developing the highest quality user experiences possible.</div>\n\n<div>• Has a killer book; you understand that explaining how and why you did the work is as important as the artifacts that show the final experience.</div>\n\n<div>We&#39;re a 50-person agency on a sunny, open floor in the heart of the Flatiron. We&#39;re twice over a 2015 Best Place to Work, from Crain&#39;s New York and AdAge. We&#39;re a UX-led shop that’s people-centric, living and breathing the total human experience to create digital work that engages every user (including ourselves). With a heavy developer influence, we&#39;re live prototyping and proof-of-concepting whatever goes out the door.</div>\n\n<div>We run a dog-friendly office and we all have lives. We think the two things that matter most are the work and the people who do it. We believe in Summer Fridays and yoga breaks. We close shop for a week in July and December. And we take Halloween very, very seriously.</div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Canceled	2016-05-26 19:30:28.292953	2016-08-10 20:00:13.010988	Cake and Arrow	Agency	f	UX Design
