672	6116750	Senior User Experience Designer	New York, New York	<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;">Senior User Experience Designer</span></strong></h1>\nOur client, a leading all-in-one marketing solution for small businesses, is looking to add two Senior User Experience Designers to their team to play a critical role on on their product teams and lead the design of user interactions for their products. They work in close partnership with team members from Product Management, Engineering, Product Marketing, Visual Design, Front End Development and others to deliver products that directly address customer needs and meet their internal business objectives.<br />\n<br />\nAs key members of the User Experience department, User Experience Designers at our client have a direct hand in creating products that engage and delight customers.  Through their pivotal role in product research and development, User Experience Designers at our client develop a deep understanding and empathy with business owners and entrepreneurs of all types.<br />\n<br />\nAt our client, User Experience Designers study customers’ behaviors and transform them into web and mobile platform experiences that are both highly functional and intuitive. The ideal candidate will have an understanding of user experience design for consumer products and will thrive in a solution-oriented environment. They will be proactive critical thinkers that work creatively through the inherent challenges of the product research and development process. They thrive as part of a cross-functional, startup team.<br />\n<br />\n<u>Responsibilities</u>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Owns the design process from product thinking, to flows, to wireframes, to prototypes, to user testing, etc.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Effectively designs interactions within the product, ranging from small feature iterations to larger, complex, greenfield experiences</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Applies best practices from the field of user experience and user research</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Is a core contributor to product discovery process and assists in validating product ideas and designs</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Supports their assigned product development team on achievement of agile sprint goals, working closely with Product Managers and Scrum Masters to prepare designs for development</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Applies an understanding of user analytics and KPIs to monitor the product’s performance and guide product evolution</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Performs user research and customer discovery, such as interviews, observation sessions, and user tests, etc.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Synthesizes and shares their research to stakeholders</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Incorporates insight from their research into product designs</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Explores new ways of communicating product design concepts and supporting information to product stakeholders</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Collaborates and critiques with fellow designers to ensure that the very best work possible is being released into the market</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<u>Qualifications</u>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Has a strong portfolio with project artifacts illustrating an individual approach to design solutions and demonstrating systematic and creative design thinking</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Has proven experience working directly with internal or external clients to gather requirements, present work, and discuss feedback</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Demonstrates aptitude for leading design projects</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Has experience successfully executing in environments that focused on conversion, renewal, subscription, etc.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Thinks about the full context of the user experience including business challenges, user needs, and technological capabilities</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Uses Sketch, Invision, Omnigraffle, Adobe Creative Suite or similar</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Understanding of HTML and CSS</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Understands fundamentals of visual design, in order to work efficiently with visual designers</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Prior experience working with Agile software development process</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">3+ years of experience in UX, Interaction Design, Product Design, or related fields, designing for web and/or mobile</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Some formal study of user experience <span style="font-size:12px;">design</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><br />\n<span style="font-size:12px;">Our client offers excellent medical benefits packages for you and your family, including a pet insurance discount. Each office location offers its own unique set of perks such as free lunch, food trucks, contests, chair massages, gym memberships, commuter benefits, and company happy hours!</span></h2>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.642943	2016-06-01 00:00:0