650	6118658	VP of User Experience	New York, New York	<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size:16px;">VP of User Experience</span></strong></h1>\nOur client, a leading all-in-one marketing solution for small businesses, is looking to bring on a VP of User Experience who will be responsible for managing a team of talented user experience designers. You will build a UX approach and define best practices in all UX disciplines while delivering on the company’s roadmap obligations on-time and on-budget. You will work in an agile environment and play a critical role in centering our client&#39;s approach around its most critical user-base. The ideal candidate will be a tireless advocate for the end user, distills complex problems into straight forward solutions, loves to collaborate and has the ability to thrive in a fast paced environment and drive for results.<br />\n<br />\n<u>Responsibilities</u><br />\n<br />\n<span style="line-height: 20.8px;">• Define and champion our strong individual- centered user experience vision and design aesthetic across the company, our customers, and our partners. </span><br />\n• Lead the vision, strategy, and execution of the user experience. Lead the user experience function end-to-end. <br />\n• Make our user experience stand out in the market and make it a key driver of our company’s market position and success. <br />\n• Define and champion the design methodologies and processes that will be used in the design and development lifecycle using the agile process. <br />\n• Grow and mentor a team of highly-skilled and highly-engaged user experience professionals. Promote overall awareness and competence in design research and design thinking, creating opportunities for the team to grow and expand their own skills and portfolios.<br />\n<br />\n<u>Qualifications</u><br />\n<br />\n• 10+ years of experience in UX, Visual Design and user research.<br />\n• 5+ years of experience leading UX teams.<br />\n• Experience working in a cloud software product company, driving design from planning to release over multiple releases.<br />\n• Experience designing for a broad set of UI platforms including web and mobile.<br />\n• Expertise across all aspects of user experience, including UX strategy, interaction design, user research/assessment, prototyping, visual design, and user adoption.<br />\n• Implemented user-centric UX best practices as part of a significant UX team.<br />\n• Experienced implementing/using UX pattern and components libraries.<br />\n• Understand UX research methods and practices.<br />\n• Concrete experience doing usability studies, personas studies, remote user-testing<br />\n• Great Information architecture skill and interaction design experience<br />\n• Deep knowledge of visual designs best practice<br />\n• Excellent organizational and communication skills<br />\n• Ability to work in a fast paced environment and communicate results to management.<br />\n• Ability to work on multiple projects with varying deadlines<br />\n• Excellent verbal, written, and interpersonal communications skills\n<h2><span style="font-size: 12px;">Our client offers excellent medical benefits packages for you and your family, including a pet insurance discount. Each office location offers its own unique set of perks such as free lunch, food trucks, contests, chair massages, gym memberships, commuter benefits, and company happy hours!</span></h2>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.427088	2016-06-01 00:00:08.266714	Yodle	In-house	t	UX Design, Product Design
625	7166652	Senior UX Designer	New York, New York	<div>Sr. User Experience Designer<br />\n </div>\n\n<div><em>Be part of a team responsible for creating fun, innovative, and usable digital content experiences for kids. Our client, a global entertainment conglomerate, is seeking a Senior Experience Designer build multiplatform experiences for their children/teen properties</em>. <br />\n </div>\n\n<div>As a Sr. User Experience Designer, you will work across scrum teams to create the next generation of industry­leading apps and sites for kids. You are equal parts visual and user experience designer, and a technology enthusiast at heart. Your portfolio should reflect your desire to innovate in the user experience space, and incorporate thoughtful, well­ informed user­-centric decision making. <br />\n </div>\n\n<div>Responsibilities</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Produce end­-to­-end UX and Design deliverables for large cross­-platform experiences. These include responsive wireframes, storyboards, prototypes that exhibit delightful animation and interactions, and high­fidelity comps.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Innovate and find opportunities to think of the next big thing.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Present and articulate design thinking in an effective manner in order to “sell” the approach to stakeholders.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Utilize your fluency through the interaction design process in order to best articulate your vision. You value prototypes over static comps. You are right at home in Photoshop, Illustrator, or Sketch, but can easily switch gears and jump into Axure, Pixate, Proto.io, After Effects, or other tools to get your concept across.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Solve problems with research and data. </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Utilize your strength as a conceptual thinker, a strong visual storyteller, and a strategist who understands the value of integrating brand narrative into your solutions.<br />\n\t </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>Requirements</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>5+ years’ experience in Interaction Design, Product Design, or User Interface Design for desktop and mobile applications</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>A strong, clean design sense that values usability, simplicity, and consistency</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>Author UX & Design artifacts including functional specs, user journeys and flows, wireframes with responsive breakpoints, sitemaps, animation prototypes, high­fidelity comps, and assets</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>Experience working with qualitative and quantitative UX research methodologies and ability to iterate on designs by integrating feedback and recommendations derived from user research</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>Experience working within an agile environment</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>Ability to create and follow interaction guidelines, style guides, and best practices when designing</div>\n\n\t<div>for new platforms, and ability to challenge and improve them when necessary</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div>Collaborative self­starter, able to work both independently or with a larger team</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.216425	2016-08-25 16:00:07.847419	Nickelodeon	In-house	t	UX Design
666	7097595	VP of Business Development and Marketing	New York, New York	<u><strong>We are:</strong></u><br />\nMotivate Design, a user experience research, design and staffing agency. With a collaborative culture centered around innovative and strategic thinking, we have been named as one Inc’s fastest growing companies two years in a row. Working with organizations such as Jet.com, Chick-fil-A, Coca Cola, and leading pharmaceutical and banking institutions, we have developed a reputation for best in class UX. With deep connections in the tech and design space, we are growing and are looking for a VP of Business Development and Marketing to help pave our growth path. Check out our website to learn more! (motivatedesign.com).<br />\n<br />\n<u><strong>The role:</strong></u><br />\nThis position will report directly to the CEO and will oversee the articulation and execution of all Business Development strategies and initiatives. You have a team of highly motivated individuals that you should mold into a well-oiled Business Development machine. The incumbent will work alongside the Directors of Design, Operations and Research in addition to the VP of UX and the VP of Finance to effectively and efficiently coordinate the company’s resources towards the end goal of scalable revenue generation.<br />\n<br />\nThe VP of Sales and Marketing will function in both a managerial and strategic fashion. You will be dealing with roadmap, strategy, process implementation, client relationships and team management, (between 3-5 team members; some direct reports, some dotted lines).<br />\n<br />\nYou will be expected to generate business through effective sales and marketing strategies, as well as overseeing the team who will be producing content and implementing processes.<br />\n<br />\n<strong><u>Primary responsibilities:</u></strong>\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Coordination of all available resources (human, financial and other) through nurturing, mentorship, guidance and strategic alignment towards effective Business Development</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Business development  (coordinating responses to opportunities from retainers, partnerships, affiliates, account management, inbound)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Product strategy (product validation, collateral, launch)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Team management (tactical, organizational)</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<u><strong>You have:</strong></u>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in agency operations and the speed at which things move (ideally in a smaller agency setting, but this is not a requirement)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Between 10-20 years of experience, with no less than 2 years of recent experience managing a team of at least 5</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A hunger to contribute to the growth of not only revenue, but overall team efficiency</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">An understanding of, or exposure to the digital media, design and development methodologies.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<u><strong>Day to day:</strong></u><br />\nDays will vary greatly. Some days will be focused on mapping out strategy and roadmaps, others will be working closely with the team to roll out plans and oversee quality and efficiency, and others will be focused on company wide collaborative sessions.<br />\n<br />\nYour job will be to self monitor and form the best strategy for pushing the busine