Strategic project leadership: experience leading projects through concept, pitch, iterative design and development, delivery, and ongoing support</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Prior experience working in an interdisciplinary team of developers, designers, and/or subject-matter experts.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to communicate with and present to stakeholders at all levels of the organization.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Undergraduate/Graduate Degree or equivalent experience in any of the following fields: Information Design, Interaction Design, User Experience, Human-Computer Interaction, Graphic design, Statistics, Quantitative Finance, Data science and Analytics.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nDesirable Skills and Experience:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Familiarity with visual analysis software e.g. Tableau Spotfire, Qlik, VisIt.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Familiarity with high-fidelity visualization prototyping tools such as d3.js, Processing, three.js, ggplot2/R, Python or similar.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Financial background or experience.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience designing for desktop & mobile and 2D & 3D data visualizations.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nApplication & Portfolio:<br />\nOur client would like to see examples of interactive data visualizations, information visualizations, or information graphics you have designed. Your visualization portfolio may include, but is not limited to: sketches, wireframes, user workflows, interactive prototypes, and production software. We are especially interested in how you have leveraged interaction to allow users to explore and understand complex datasets. Please include at least two projec