rgin: 0;">Take art direction from creative leads</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Produce design comps, specifications, and prototypes</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Contribute to product ideation and concept development</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Participate as a member of an interdisciplinary team that includes creative leads, other designers, project managers, and software developers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;"><u>Requirements</u></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">At least 3 years of design production and user interface design experience</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Mastery of design tools such as PhotoShop, Illustrator, and Flash</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Knowledge of user interface design processes and methodology, particularly as applied to web-based and mobile applications</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Knowledge of capabilities and limitations of web technologies such as HTML, JavaScript, and CSS</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor’s degree in graphics design, user experience design, fine arts, or a related design discipline</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;"><br />\n<u>Candidate Profile</u></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to move at hyper-startup-speed in a high-energy environment with high expectations.</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work independently and quickly, but cares about precision and details, doing whatever it takes to get the job done.</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to estimate, plan, and prioritize own design and production work</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Extremely detail oriented</li>\n\t<li style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Passion for creating great user experiences</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 1.2em;"><u>The Team</u><br />\nFounded by an experienced group of entrepreneurs from successful start-ups (Uber, Teladoc, Gilt, One Medical Group, Buzzfeed), we are passionate about improving access to high quality and personal health care.</div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.234977	2016-09-22 20:00:09.369641	Pager	\N	t	\N
653	7249461	Senior UI Visual Designer	New York, NY	Are you inspired by the prospect of crafting elegant, sophisticated user interfaces for cutting-edge B2B technology? Do you have a passion for great SaaS products, and a desire to delight customers? We’re looking for a talented Snr. UI Visual Designer to work with our User Experience Design Department -who would be responsible for helping us design, and evolve innovative, visually pleasing SaaS (Software as Service) web-based applications. You will be responsible for the visual design of best-in-class, data-heavy and <br />\nvisually complex, sophisticated B2B experiences. <br />\n<br />\nYou will work closely with UX / Interaction Designers, product management and UI developers from early stage product concepts to launch as part of the team in an agile environment. You are a pragmatic visionary who can <br />\ntranslate business needs into elegant customer-focused solutions. You must be proactive, responsive, organized, professional, flexible and able to succeed within an open and collaborative peer environment. The ideal candidate for this position will be comfortable visualizing an experience in the abstract and driving that vision into solid design deliverables while working in collaboration with the product team and user experience design leadership.<br />\n<br />\nThe Sr. UI Visual Designer’s responsibility would be to enhance and polish wireframes and rough mockups while following a Brand / UI Styleguide. The Sr. UI Visual Designer will need to produce production assets in Adobe Creative Suite (mostly Photoshop & Illustrator) and interact with front-end UI Developers. The Sr. UI Visual Designer will need to be skilled at iconography, creating style-guides, designing for various complex B2B SaaS UI components, and provide specifications when needed.<br />\n<br />\nWe are looking for a creative and skilled world-class designer who can take our wireframes & mockups and make them shine, put on the finishing touches, and enhance them to beautifully polished UIs. Someone who can contribute sophisticated new ideas that will set our UIs apart from the competition.<br />\n \n<div><strong>Key Skills and Responsibilities;</strong><br />\n<br />\n• Help visualize, communicate, and implement the user interface design and associated assets on a range of the company’s SaaS       products<br />\n<br />\n• Think strategically to design consistently innovative, but simple solutions to challenging problems<br />\n<br />\n• Help us create elegant and effective customer experiences and effective visuals that support and reinforce the company’s vision, user experience design and brand image<br />\n<br />\n• Create UI assets as needed such as icons, widgets, UI components, keep things organized, labeled and structured in logical hierarchies, file organization and versioning backup<br />\n<br />\n• Partner and collaborate with front-end UI developers, provide UI specifications, support and follow-through to make sure the       implemented UI reflects visual designs “pixel-perfect”<br />\n<br />\n• Continue to evolve our UI Styleguide and Standards and design pattern libraries as needed<br />\n<br />\n• Be the keeper of the brand look-and-feel and ensure all visual designs across all channels live up to the highest quality and best-in-class visual standard<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Basic Qualifications;</strong><br />\n<br />\n• At least 5+ years of experience as a visual UI designer for interactive digital products<br />\n<br />\n• A portfolio that demonstrates B2B stylistic breadth for diverse media<br />\n<br />\n• Excellent communication, presentation, interpersonal and analytical skills, including the ability to communicate complex, interactive design concepts clearly and persuasively to internal teams<br />\n<br />\n• Be able to defend designs, clearly articulating your design decisions to various teams<br />\n<br />\n• Attention to detail and a deep understanding of color-psychology, color-schemes and typography <br />\n<br />\n• Understanding of direction without much hand-holding, self-managed, organized and accountable for <br />\ndeliverables with a good work-ethic and self-discipline<br />\n<br />\n• Expert skill level in Adobe Creative Suite (especially Photoshop), comfortable with inDesign<br />\n<br />\n• Bachelor’s degree in graphic/ visual design or equivalent solid, demonstrable professional experience<br />\n<br />\n• A Mac user with deep knowledge of using Mac OSX (our Design Dept. is all Mac)<br />\n<br />\n• If remote, need to have a high-speed internet connection as we video conference and Skype Preferred Qualifications (big pluses, jump to the front of the line)<br />\n<br />\n• At least 2-3 years in B2B, enterprise SaaS application UI design<br />\n<br />\n• Solid understanding of web-technologies that underlie dynamic interactive experiences<br />\n<br />\n• Team player with refined and assertive skills - ability to positively influence change through inspirational design, solid rationale, supporting data and diplomacy<br />\n<br />\n• Knowledge of information architecture, usability standards and UI design best practices<br />\n<br />\n• Ability to work cross-team and synthesize feedback and input from Interaction Designers, product management, engineering and UI developers<br />\n<br />\n• Committed to learning and expanding professional and technical knowledge<br />\n<br />\n• Interested in and motivated by great UX</div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.453229	2016-06-01 00:00:08.461129	PubMatic	Startup	t	UI Design
664	5045333	User Experience Designer	San Francisco, CA	<div dir="ltr">​Our client, (a successful 12 year-old SaaS based company located inside San Francisco), is seeking a User Experience Designer to join their team and help them bring world-class user experiences to their customers. They have over 50 million users in countries around the world and are just getting started!</div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr">--About the Job--</div>\n\n<div dir="ltr">You will be an integral part of both a project team and the overall User Experience team, able to flex your design muscle and grow as a designer.  Our client likes people who &#39;bring great design chops to the table but also bring a point-of-view about design and stretch our understanding of design&#39;.</div>\n \n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Work with product managers and other stakeholders to understand the roadmap and priorities.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Collaborate with a paired designer, engineers and product managers to drive from problem to idea to design to launch.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Design functional yet elegant and beautiful experiences.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Share your works-in-progress with the rest of the design team to get feedback, identify related experiences, and assure a cohesive ecosystem.</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr">--Team Structure--<br />\nThere is a dedicated research team, and the rest of the team are designers with a T-shaped skill set. Our client does not believe in silo&#39;ing disciplines.<br />\n<br />\n--About You--</div>\n\n<div dir="ltr">Our client is not just looking for a designer. Of course, it’s important that you have design chops, but they also want someone who’s &#39;fun to work with and can challenge the team and help us grow&#39;.</div>\n \n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">You’re a generalist with depth in detailed design or a specialist looking to broaden your skills.  They understand that designers tend to come with a diverse set of skills and backgrounds. They&#39;re interested in talented designers first, titles a distant second.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">You’ve shipped product. You understand that it’s only partly about finding a good solution to a problem and that much of your job as a designer is to work within the constraints of the business, the technology, and time.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">You “solve” within context. You care about the users, who they are, what they are trying to do. You also care about the brand and what it is trying to accomplish. You seek to understand things like users’ needs and behaviors, and how your designs affect the bottom line.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Prototyping is part of your toolkit. You like to “feel” concepts and designs to see if there’s a there there and where you can refine. You’ve also found it an incredibly good tool for telling the story of your designs to your coworkers and users.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">You understand that there’s code behind your designs. Whether it’s the HTML and CSS that drives your designs, or the engine underneath the hood, you want to understand the capabilities and limitations so you can leverage the technology effectively in your designs. Bonus points if you can get your hands dirty in the front-end code.</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">You want to work as part of a team. That means working with other designers, product managers, engineers, and researchers to brainstorm and find the best solutions for the problem set. It means sharing and learning from each other. It means you’re fun to work with.</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr">--Benefits--</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Pre-IPO Stock</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Competitive Salary</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Comprehensive Health Benefits</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">401k Program</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Commuter Benefits</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Fully Stocked Kitchen</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Paid Time Off for Volunteering</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	On Hold	2016-05-26 19:30:28.530424	2016-06-01 00:00:08.191004	DocuSign	\N	t	\N
623	6947577	Product Designer	New York, NY	<section>\n<div>\n<div><strong>Product Designer for Biz Applications Startup Founded by Google, Facebook, and Big Data Alums</strong><br />\n <br />\nA tight-knit, world-class 20-person team devoted to turning complex technologies into real, bottom-line business solutions. Founders from Google, Facebook, and a Big Data pioneer. Weekly lunches and fun, take-a-load-off, team-building activities. Steps from the subway.<br />\n <br />\nHard to pass up, right?<br />\n <br />\nThis 2-year old startup—loaded with funding from well-known investing partners, including Sequoia Capital, and Fortune 500 clients—needs a <strong>UX Designer</strong> to help design and build data-driven, marketing-centric business applications that drive revenue. Everyone here is mad about data—about optimized system performance and tackling complicated algorithmic problems. Ideally, you should be, too.<br />\n <br />\nThis is a “full-stack” design position—responsible for research, design, <em>and need to</em> have knowledge of development. This is a young company and everyone else is a jack-of-all-trades, get-your-hands-wet member of the team.<br />\n <br />\nWorking with the Head of Product Design and a team of nimble engineers (you need to know how to speak ‘engineer’), you’ll develop prototypes based on user research, which you’ll be heavily involved with—and not just developing prototypes, validating concepts, and translating data into design. You’ll organize and conduct user research studies, too. They’d love your help talking up to non-designers the benefits and components of what good design looks like.<br />\n <br />\nThey’re looking for someone with at least 4 years of experience designing interfaces and shipping web applications, PLUS an academic degree in Human Computer Interaction, Interaction Design, or something similar. Do you get a kick out of making complex data look simple? Perfect!<br />\n <br />\nYou should know how to develop interactive prototypes in your sleep, and the ins and outs of UX and UI design processes and methodologies. Be prepared to show you’re familiar with agile process development and working with engineers. Remember: speak engineer! UI libraries are already in place, but you must show experience in building prototypes. Familiarity with HTML, CSS, jQuery, JavaScript is nice, but not critical; and though you won’t be coding, knowledge of code is helpful.<br />\n <br />\nIn such a small organization, everyone’s a self-starter and you should be, too. You should show that you’ve come up with original ideas and fresh approaches—and transformed them into something beautiful, but also useful and valuable. It goes without saying that your portfolio is stunning. But it should demonstrate how your designs have addressed and resolved user needs across a variety of contexts. And it can’t hurt to let your passion for the power of data visualization shine through!<br />\n <br />\nAbove all, you need to show empathy for all your different audiences and recognize the big picture: that projects are all about the user and that good design is nothing if it doesn’t advance brand and business goals.</div>\n</div>\n</section>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Active (1)	2016-05-26 19:30:28.198091	2017-01-11 01:00:08.395291	Action IQ	Startup	t	Product Design
642	6629493	UX Lead	New York, NY	<div dir="ltr"><font color="#000000">Our Client, a streaming TV and movie service that was launched in 2009, has grown to become a leader in its space in a few short years. Today, they offer hundreds of series, variety shows, movies and even kids programming in multiple languages. Their passionate audience is rapidly growing around the world, and is available in more countries than ever before. With a UX team of about 5, they are looking to add a UX Lead to focus on team structure, best practices, hands-on design work and mentorship.</font><br />\n </div>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>Definition of the role:</strong></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr">Be responsible for building up and shaping the UX team.</div>\n\n<ul dir="ltr">\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bring better cross-team collaboration through the implementation of best practices in research, product definition and prototyping.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">​Provide insight and experience to successfully manage and delegate design work across the team</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Invested in the growth of the UX team through the shaping of culture and process</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Oversees projects to support individual designers.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">​Mentor and manage team members and their growth.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>What will your day to day look like?</strong></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr">Actively involved in discussions with stakeholders to have broad understanding and knowledge of the business and current state of our range of products.</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Integrate UX process throughout the entire lifecycle of our products.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Lead by example by being hands on with important projects to help shape the broad strokes, introduce a solidified process through different methodologies and ideas in order to improve our current workflow</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>What are our expectations from a UX Lead?</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Leading the effort to define a UX process/framework that works for the team and the company.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Evangelizing UX-centric process</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Able to efficiently and effectively get up to speed and on board onto projects</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Communicative & organized – understands cross-functional team dynamics</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Not a gatekeeper/micro manager – function as a coach to support and empower each individual designer and create a strong and positive design environment for the team.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Advocate for our users – working closely with the customer service and product teams to understand our users and be able to articulate their needs to the rest of the company</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Opinionated yet adaptable – has the experience and confidence in their approach yet able to understand varying contexts for each projects and adapt their methods and skills accordingly.</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>Hard requirements:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">5+ years of experience</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Tech savvy – up-to-date on tech and design, and intuitively understands the various touch points required to shape a product</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Basic understanding of code/programming to understand platform and technical constraints, to assist in better communication between designers and developers</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Strong problem solver and storyteller – natural ability to articulate and communicate design decisions both written and oral, and can effectively lead sessions/meetings.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Ideally a T shaped designer – has a core focus in skillset with the ability to bridge the gaps between various disciplines (product management, development, marketing and business)  </div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Experienced in shaping products through its entire lifecycle – from research and strategy through build, analysis, and iteration.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Able to multitask in a fast-paced team environment.</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Must be a culture and personality fit, as well as having a team focused mindset</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Portfolio must clearly illustrate their process and point of view as a designer rather than just final outcome of projects.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><br />\n<strong>Nice to Haves:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Experience managing a design team</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Agency or startup experience</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Streaming video experience</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">OTT experience</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Agile experience</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Familiarity with a modern tech stack, including HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, Angular, JQuery, etc</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Intuition for strategy and business goals of the company (understanding KPIs, metrics, user requirements and their impact on business decisions)</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>Career development and growth opportunities:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Opportunity to lead a motivated team</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Actively part of hiring decisions, influence and impact to build up a strong ux team</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Building a user-centric process and team culture</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Exciting opportunity to work on multiple verticals and breadth of platforms and verticals (agency/product shop combined into an in-house design team)</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Product ownership </div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><strong>Qualities we value:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Hungry to grow and willing to continuously learn and fill in their own gaps</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Passionate about team and culture</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Opinionated yet **adaptable**</div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr">Excellent communicator (oral and written)</div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	On Hold	2016-05-26 19:30:28.368641	2016-06-01 00:00:08.330462	Dramafever	\N	f	\N
677	6923895	UX Designer	Redwood City, CA	Mid-Level Interaction Designer<br />\n<br />\nAs an Interaction Designer, you will work side-by-side on a team of designers, developers, and product owners to help define a world-class advertising technology transactional experience for our publisher and advertising industry customers.<br />\n<br />\nOur teams are small and nimble, giving you the freedom to make meaningful and measurable improvements to our products. Our Interaction Designers uncover, analyze, understand, and communicate to other stakeholders the product and optimum workflow requirements of our customers. <br />\n<br />\nYou care about making a great product and are able to design in an iterative process in an agile environment to uncover the best solution. You work well in a multi-disciplinary team environment, designing great solutions for end users. Your process includes research, best practices, following style guides and maintaining/building component libraries. You have worked across the full cycle of the interaction design process with deep experience in sketching, wireframes, and mockups. Bonus if you have experience in early ideation with product managers and UX Team members, user task-flow and workflow analysis, and prototyping. You have strong communication skills from presenting your ideas to managing visual designers and directing UI developers. <br />\n<br />\nYou should be knowledgeable about the competitive space, understand established design patterns and design with best practices in mind. Experience or interest in design for enterprise B2B technologies, data visualization, reporting, charts is a must. You understand the challenges and complexity of industrial strength transactional design. <br />\n<br />\nThe Contribution; <br />\n• Working with fellow UX team members and product owners plan, prioritize, coordinate, conduct task analysis and conceptual interaction modeling. Construct optimum information architecture and interaction design using industry standard tools such as OmniGraffle, Balsamiq, Axure and Adobe Creative Suite Applications. <br />\n<br />\n• Produce user requirements specifications, personas, storyboards, scenarios, flowcharts, design prototypes, and design specifications. <br />\n<br />\n• Effectively communicate conceptual ideas, detailed design, and design rationale both verbally and visually. Be ready to defend you design decisions with product owners and the UX team.<br />\n<br />\n• Manage the design process, drive decisions, track issues, and assist in estimating resource needs and schedules. <br />\n<br />\n• Work closely with development teams to ensure that design specifications are implemented. <br />\n<br />\n• Participate as a contributor to an interdisciplinary team that includes other designers, project management, business and brand strategists, and hardware and software developers. <br />\n<br />\nSuccess; <br />\nSuccess in this role means success in delivering results through teamwork and a relentless focus on what’s best for our customers. Success means continually holding oneself to the highest of professional and ethical standards and demanding the same of co-workers. Success is walking into every work day with an unwavering belief that you can and do influence affairs for the better and that in turn you will stand to reap the rewards both financially and professionally that your contribution merits. <br />\n<br />\nYou Are; <br />\nSomeone who wants to influence your own development. You’re looking for a company where you have the opportunity to pursue your interests across functions and geographies, and where a job title is not considered the final definition of who you are, but the starting point. You bring to the organization the following competencies; <br />\n<br />\n• 3-5 years interaction design experience. <br />\n<br />\n• Strong knowledge of user interface design processes and user-centered design methodology, particularly as applied to Web-based  applications (Enterprise SaaS, B2B model). <br />\n<br />\n• Strong project management, organization skills, team communications and people skills. <br />\n<br />\n• Proficiency with design and prototyping tools such as OmniGraffle, Balsamiq, Axure, Adobe Creative Suite Applications and a      willingness to explore new tools. <br />\n<br />\n• Knowledge of capabilities and limitations of Web technologies such as HTML, JavaScript, and CSS. <br />\n<br />\n• A degree in Human-Computer Interaction or a related design or behavioral science discipline is a big plus. <br />\n<br />\n• A passion for creating high-quality products and awesome user experiences in the enterprise space that resonates with people.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.673587	2016-06-01 00:00:08.349572	PubMatic	\N	t	\N
635	6084269	Director of UX	Santa Monica, CA	<h2 style="text-align: center;">Director of UX</h2>\n\n<div style="text-align: center;"><em>We are honored to represent our client, a premier video game studio, in their search for a Director of User Experience.  This is an exceptional opportunity to lead and innovate in a space that is committed to seamless, best-in-class user experiences across their entire ecosystem.</em><br />\n </div>\n\n<div><span style="font-size:18px;">Responsibilities:</span></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with other UX and product leaders to shape UX strategy, establishing consistent quality standards while maintaining a culture of continuous evolution</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Create big-picture experiential strategies that cross numerous touch points unconstrained by platforms and technologies and work iteratively to put them into action; set a vision that encompasses the entire experiential ecosystem, including mobile apps, live event stage designs, product features or anything else that impacts the overall player experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Advise and mentor UX team members, collaborating with Lead UX Designers and other UX Directors to share knowledge, set realistic goals and seek out challenges and experiential opportunities</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ensure experiential consistency and by setting flexible design principles and evangelizing them throughout the organization</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Build collaborative relationships with thought leaders across the studio and work with cross-functional teams to build fresh, but accessible UX solutions</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span style="font-size:18px;">You are:</span></h2>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>A UX strategy veteran:</strong> you have 8+ years experience building large-scale experience and product visions, at least four of which you spent leading and inspiring the teams responsible for delivering them</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Curious and open-minded:</strong> you’ve probably supplemented your experience with a bachelor’s or master’s degree; you know education doesn’t end just because you’ve stepped out of the classroom, and view every challenge as an opportunity to learn something new</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Strategically adaptive:</strong> you thrive in rapidly-evolving, ambiguous environments where you can work independently and stretch your creative muscles to find imaginative solutions; you know a great idea can come from anywhere, and rapidly change gears to adapt to shifting business or player needs</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Business and user-centric</strong>: you use user-centered design principles to shape UX strategy and positively impact both business goals and the player experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Product insightful:</strong> you use a combination of experience, research and intuition to set an ambitious quality bar and inspire team members to  overcome obstacles and explore imaginative solutions in pursuit of UX perfection</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>A team leader</strong>: you know the best leaders build on a strong foundation of trust that inspires teammates to explore imaginative solutions in pursuit of quality results; you lead by example, and use your knowledge and experience to help teammates level up their UX skills as you work alongside them</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>An effective storyteller: </strong>you know how to win people over to your point of view, and craft compelling stories that champion experience design principles throughout Riot</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>A game-culture empath:</strong> you might not call yourself a gamer, but you’re highly empathic to game culture and eager to dive in and learn more about Riot and its game products; you’re able to quickly align with the priorities of a new community by immersing yourself in the culture to understand their wants and needs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Responsibilities:</h2>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with other UX and product leaders to shape UX strategy, establishing consistent quality standards while maintaining a culture of continuous evolution</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Create big-picture experiential strategies that cross numerous touch points unconstrained by platforms and technologies and work iteratively to put them into action; set a vision that encompasses the entire experiential ecosystem, including mobile apps, live event stage designs, product features or anything else that impacts the overall player experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Advise and mentor UX team members, collaborating with Lead UX Designers and other UX Directors to share knowledge, set realistic goals and seek out challenges and experiential opportunities</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ensure experiential consistency and by setting flexible design principles and evangelizing them throughout the organization</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Build collaborative relationships with thought leaders across the studio and work with cross-functional teams to build fresh, but accessible UX solutions</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N