695	6235286	Senior UX Researcher	San Francisco, CA	​Our client, (a successful 12 year-old SaaS based company located inside San Francisco), is seeking a User Experience Researcher to join their team and help them bring world-class user experiences to their customers. They have over 50 million users in countries around the world and are just getting started!<br />\n \n<div><strong>About the Job</strong></div>\n\n<div>You&#39;ll be responsible for:</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Executing a variety of research studies, using both generative and evaluative methods.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Supporting the design and development of web and mobile experiences while promoting customer empathy across development teams.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Working independently with designers, product managers and other stakeholders to identify research needs.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Designing and executing research using appropriate methods including usability studies, surveys and ethnographic research.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Synthesizing findings into meaningful themes and presenting those stories and insights to a variety of audiences.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Making design recommendations based on research findings, knowledge of web and mobile design patterns, usability heuristics and understanding of cognitive processes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div> </div>\n\n<div><strong>About You</strong></div>\n\n<div>You might be the person we&#39;re looking for if:</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>You have extensive experience designing and conducting user research</strong> related to enterprise software or service design. You&#39;ve conducted research supporting all phases of the product development lifecycle<strong>.</strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>You can make your data come alive. </strong>You care about the users, who they are, and what they are trying to do, and you can communicate users&#39; needs and aspirations to developers, marketers and product managers. You understand that that research insights are most valuable when they&#39;re accompanied with relevant recommendations that work within the constraints of the business, the technology, and time.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>You can swiftly improvise and revise research plans as needed</strong>, to think strategically and develop creative solutions to research challenges, and a proven track record of working well with developers, product managers, designers and business partners</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>You want to work as part of a team.</strong> That means working with other researchers, designers, product managers, and engineers -- brainstorming with them to identify and design solutions, and identifying ways to improve their decisions with user data.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div><strong>Ideal candidates will also have:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience working with in an Agile development environment.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Familiarity with Morae, web analytics, A/B and multivariate testing methodologies.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">An advanced degree in human interaction, cognitive science, or related field.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong>Benefits</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Pre-IPO Stock</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Competitive Salary</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Comprehensive Health Benefits</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">401k Program</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Commuter Benefits</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Fully Stocked Kitchen</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Paid Time Off for Volunteering</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.790339	2016-06-01 00:00:09.746172	DocuSign	\N	t	\N
728	5778377	UX Designer	Plymouth Meeting, PA	Our client is a rapidly growing company with the goal of helping clients get better health care in a way that delights them and saves them and their employer money. They achieve this by simplifying the complex array of health care and health benefit services that large Fortune 500 corporations offer to their employees. <br />\n<br />\n<strong>About the Team and Environment:</strong><br />\nThe Engagement Technology Group is delivering next-generation consumer engagement solutions for healthcare using an AWS cloud infrastructure.  <br />\n<br />\nTheir stack is Java on the Play framework on the back-end, and HTML5/CSS3/JavaScript on the front-end (including mobile).  The entire development environment is managed in the cloud utilizing tools and services such as GitHub, Jira on Demand, Bamboo, and Amazon Web Services.<br />\n<br />\nOur client cares deeply about aesthetics and is laser focused on creating an experience for their users that sets the bar high in an industry not known for elegant software.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Role Overview: </strong><br />\nLet&#39;s face it... when people think "healthcare," they don&#39;t necessarily think "fun and exciting." The challenge for the UX team is to take complex data and make it simple, relevant and meaningful for everyday people (millions of people in fact).<br />\n<br />\nOur clients&#39; UX team members apply user experience design, visual design, research, and prototyping to develop the best solutions for our end users. Since user-centric design is critical to our product development process, the team is fully integrated with Engineering to shape our products. We know that our ability to motivate and educate customers drives better healthcare outcomes, so we use our insights from customer research to design engaging products that inspire real, positive action. <br />\n<br />\n<strong>Your role:</strong><br />\nAs a User Experience Designer, you&#39;ll take the lead in designing intuitive, compelling products that change the way people think about their health and how they can affect the overall health of themselves and their loved ones. You&#39;ll have the challenge of working on designs across multiple channels, including web, email, small/mobile devices, and SMS. You&#39;ll be a design leader throughout the entire product cycle - including conception, rapid prototyping, usability testing, development, post-launch research. You&#39;ll work on cross-functional teams and collaborate frequently with the Executive Team and Engineers. <br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />\n•    Own UX design for parts of product suite, including printed reports, web, mobile, email and devices<br />\n•    Explore UI solutions, create UX flows, build wireframes, write specs for developers<br />\n•    Collaborate with Engineering to create the best and simplest possible solutions for the user that fall within product constraints<br />\n•    Lead usability testing and incorporate findings into designs<br />\n•    Participate in Agile QA<br />\n•    Be a true advocate for the user and help drive the UX roadmap<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Required Qualifications:</strong><br />\n•    You have a BA/BS/MS in HCI, Design, or related field<br />\n•    You&#39;re a UX designer first and foremost, but have some other skills as well - you can put on your prototyping hat and build a lean, mean web prototype, (no not need to have advanced visual design capabilities, though).<br />\n•    You jump at the chance to sketch, post-it, mind map, and brainstorm to solve problems<br />\n•    You love diving into the details<br />\n•    You are comfortable and experienced leading user research and testing sessions on your designs<br />\n•    You are a master at time management<br />\n•    Experience working with the Agile development process is a plus	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.047777	2016-06-01 00:00:09.672062	Accolade	\N	t	\N
741	5038588	Director/Manager, Finance & Operations	New York, New York	<strong><u>MOTIVATE DESIGN </u></strong><br />\n <br />\n<strong>Title: Director/Manager, Finance & Operations</strong><br />\n<strong>Reports To: Chief Executive Officer</strong><br />\n<strong>Location: New York City</strong><br />\n <br />\nMotivate Design, a leading small UX Design and Research firm in NYC, Boston and San Francisco, has enjoyed tremendous growth since our inception five years ago.  We are seeking a collaborative, finance expert and multi-tasker to join our family of Motivators and help guide our company through it’s continuing growth and prosperity.<br />\n <br />\n <br />\n<strong><u>Job Summary</u></strong><br />\n <br />\nThe Director/Manager (title is negotiable!) of Finance & Operations works closely with the CEO, the senior team in providing strategic and thought leadership to create value and long term success.  He/She has overall responsibility for financial planning and financial operations in maintaining a strong internal control across all disciplines of the agency.  The individual partners with the senior team to ensure that the organization efficiently and effectively delivers on its financial goals and initiatives.   Additionally, he/she acts as a liaison between the agency and ADP TotalSource in management of payroll and HR compliance.  He/She must be able to set appropriate priorities, communicate well with staff at all levels, business partners, and clients in addition to possessing high computer aptitude and business acumen.<br />\n <br />\n \n<div> </div>\n<strong><u>Job Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\n <br />\n<strong><em>Financial Planning & Analysis</em></strong><em> – Anticipate risks and initiate actions to achieve financial goals</em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Prepare the annual business plan, taking into account business initiatives and financial target</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Prepare monthly rolling forecasts as deemed necessary to maintain visibility on full year financial performance</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Analyze actual performance against key benchmarks and highlight variances, trends, etc</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Provide management with information regarding financial and operational performance of individual business segments against internal KPIs</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\n<strong><em>Financial & Human Resource Operations</em></strong><em> – </em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Provide financial guidance to capability leads to assess financial risk/benefit of operational initiatives, client profitability, staffing allocation</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Provide “what if” analysis to management, with corresponding financial impact</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Liaise with capability leads with development of client contracts, remuneration strategies (i.e. functional hourly rates, project profitability, pricing models, sensitivity analysis, etc.) and interaction/negotiations with client procurement, including implementation of particular client billing arrangements and fee reconciliations</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Liaise with ADP TotalSource in management of payroll, procuring medical & dental benefits, 401K, and ensure agency is HR compliance.</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\n<strong><em>Financial Reporting & Control</em></strong><em> – Ensure that monthly & annual statutory reporting is performed accurately</em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Perform all areas of financial reporting, particularly revenue recognition and provisions for risks & charges</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Partner with agency’s accountants to ensure accurate and timely reporting of year end financials to local authority</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ensure compliance of GAAP in working with agency’s accounting team</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Oversea supplier management in issuance of purchase orders, validation of invoices including contractors & third party vendors; and ensure timely accounts payable</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Lead and coordinate all audits including client and regulatory audits</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Manage internal expense reimbursement process in validating receipts, and payment to all staff members</li>\n</ul>\n <strong style="line-height: 1.6;"><em><u>Key Competencies  </u></em></strong><br />\n <br />\nKey competencies that are required to be successful in the role:<br />\n \n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Financial Planning & Analysis</strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Contract Negotiation </strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Decision Quality</strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Strategic & Innovative</strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Multi-tasking and wearing different hats</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Business Acumen</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Communicates effectively</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Managing/Mentoring staff</li>\n</ul>\n <strong style="line-height: 1.6;"><em><u>Job Requirements</u></em></strong><span style="line-height: 1.6;">   </span><br />\n <br />\n<em>Essential</em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Education: Bachelor’s degree required, MBA or CPA preferred</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><strong>Agency experience</strong></li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">7+ years of experience in managing an accounting/finance department</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Speak fluent English</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong Excel competency and knowledge of Quickbook</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong interpersonal and communication skills</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work autonomously</li>\n</ul>\n