726	4090257	Director, Web and Interaction Design	New York, NY	<u><strong>Director, Web and Interaction Design</strong></u><br />\n<br />\nA leading aspirational e-commerce site specializing in luxury and one-of-a-kind products is adding a Director of Interaction and Web Design to their team. It has become the go-to source for the world&#39;s leading interior designers and consumers to find antiques, vintage furniture, jewelry, vintage fashion and fine art.<br />\n <br />\nWith strong financial backing, our client is a unique blend of expert curators and seasoned Internet executives from companies including Ebay, Gilt, Google, FreshDirect, Mlb.com and Twitter.<br />\n<br />\nOur Product organization strives to build the most compelling and intuitive experiences for our customers. We are seeking a Director of Interaction and Web Design to help scale and build our team.<br />\n<br />\nAs the Director of our Interaction and Web Design team, you will be leading a talented group of interaction designers, web designers and user research interns. Candidates should possess a passion for great design, a strong aesthetic sensibility, and the ability to design simple solutions to complex problems. You should also be able to manage projects as well as people.<br />\n<br />\nAs a member of our leadership team, you will partner with various members of our Product Management organization along with other departments to build the most compelling product experiences. Candidates must be creative problem solvers, innovative designers, and passionate user advocates. You must also thrive in a fast-paced, team-based, and results-focused environment.<br />\n<br />\n<u>Job Requirements</u><br />\n•    Manage and mentor a team of talented interaction designers (including UI/visual) and user researchers.<br />\n•    Develop design processes that will help the team scale and produce well-considered designs.<br />\n•    Work with team to produce our user experience strategy and develop next generation concepts.<br />\n•    Contribute significantly to strategic design initiatives, from defining our style guidelines, mobile design strategy to site architecture for consumer seller facing experiences.<br />\n•    Partner with a wide range of stakeholders from concept to creation, including product managers, marketing, user research, developers, and testing.<br />\n•    Comfortable in an agile environment of rapid iteration and experimentation, prototyping at various levels of fidelity.<br />\n•    Have command of various applications related to prototyping and user interface design (Indesign, Photoshop, Illustrator, Omnigraffle, etc).<br />\n•    Possess strong verbal, written and visual presentation skills with a deep understanding of the value in storytelling.<br />\n•    Well versed in collaborative design techniques, rapid prototyping, UI design, UI patterns, time-based visual design and information architecture.<br />\n•    Aware of current trends in design patterns, information visualization and current web technologies such as HTML 5, CSS3, Javascript, gestural UI, animation, etc.<br />\n•    At least 7+ years of experience designing consumer facing web applications<br />\n•    3+ years of managing/mentoring junior designers<br />\n<br />\n<u>Education</u><br />\nAdvanced degree in Human Computer Interaction, Design, or other related discipline preferred<br />\n<br />\n<u>Extras</u>\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><u>​</u>Unlimited paid time off,</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Weekly white linen lunches,</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Snacks,</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Full benefits & 401k</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Paid family leave</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Commuter benefits</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">In-office yoga</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.037511	2016-06-01 00:00:09.465356	1stDibs	\N	t	\N
711	5440771	VP, Insights  - UX Research	New York, New York	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong> Vice President, Insights</strong></div>\n<strong>Our parent company, Motivate Design, a leading, UX Research and Design agency in NYC led by Mona Patel, noted practitioner, lecturer and author, is looking for an accomplished, knowledgeable and passionate researcher to join our firm in a leadership position.</strong><br />\n <br />\nAs Vice President, Insights,  your primary responsibilities are to develop the strategic direction for projects and to provide leadership and guidance to the research team to execute the strategy.<br />\n<br />\nSecondary responsibilities include supporting business development and thought leadership efforts<strong>, </strong>reporting current status of projects/client relationships as necessary to Executive Leadership Team and working regularly with Business & Financial Directors on the progress of projects weekly <br />\n<br />\n<strong>Key Activities</strong><br />\n<strong>Project - To the project <br />\nExecuting to the boundaries of the project in a way that is credible and quality-driven</strong><br />\n·       Lead the process of defining the problem space with the client<br />\n·       Help define requirements and constraints for key projects<br />\n·       Work with Motivate business lead to develop project frameworks (i.e., methodologies, resourcing, phasing)<br />\n·       Work hands-on with Motivate Design’s design team to leverage facts and activate research insights that lead to smarter solutions<br />\n·       Present strategies and work-in-progress to stakeholders and build consensus<br />\n·       Provide day-to-day leadership and guidance to the research team and ensure that the approaches being explored are high quality and on-strategy<br />\n·       Work hands-on to create research artifacts where appropriate and necessary<br />\n<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Strategic - Beyond the project<br />\nDelivering beyond the boundaries of the project at hand, establishing next steps for future collaboration</strong><br />\n·       Develop and hone research methodologies; support and challenge Head in crafting strategies for addressing overall UX goals<br />\n·       Provide insight into the value, purpose, and tactics of each phase of the Motivate process<br />\n·       Strong and in-depth knowledge of established design thinking with the ability to identify the right approach or opportunities for new thought leadership<br />\n·       Work closely with clients to address internal limitations and challenges that may present themselves during the discovery, strategy, and design process<br />\n·       Lead and inspire teams to dig deeper into complex qualitative and quantitative data sets (including limitations based on the data)<br />\n<strong>Internal - To the business<br />\nBettering the inner workings of the business and personnel</strong><br />\n·       Support business development efforts by leading select scoping exercises and making sales presentations<br />\n·       Mentor company staff on UX/research objectives, processes, and philosophies<br />\n·       Identify efficiencies within the business’ body of knowledge, tools of the trade, and techniques that can be applied to other projects<br />\n·       Lead internal teams to articulate and publicize their perspectives on UX/research<br />\n <br />\n<strong>External - Beyond the business<br />\nMoving the brand forward, and thinking about its context in the greater business environment</strong><br />\n·       Guide the team to share and express philosophies around UX/research<br />\n·       Support thought leadership efforts by contributing to blog posts and white papers, attending and speaking at industry events, and leading knowledge sharing sessions within the agency<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Requirements </strong><br />\n<strong>Technical Skills</strong><br />\n·       Strong background in research methodologies, strategy, user research, and experience design<br />\n·       Demonstrated ability to conduct, lead, and educate others in various research approaches<br />\n·       Ability to manage or weigh in on personnel, scoping, and financials as necessary <br />\n<strong>Soft Skills</strong><br />\n·       Leadership and business skills that evoke confidence and a strong sense of direction<br />\n·       Storytelling and public speaking: both verbal and visual communication<br />\n·       Resourceful and capable of offering new directions and concepts crucial to establishing trust with clients<br />\n·       Embraces ambiguity, failure, and the iterative design process<br />\n·       Ability to work in systems, applications, and processes that require adaptability to the client/project needs<br />\n·       Flexible and understanding of the intensive nature of research and consulting (i.e., travel, peaks/valleys of work)<br />\n·       Naturally empathic and curious about the lived realities of all human beings; eager to approach all projects with an objective perspective<br />\n·       Reflexive, and able to acknowledge personal bias or assumptions that may influence projects, strategies, or philosophies<br />\n·       Insatiable curiosity for new techniques, methods, technologies, beliefs, and expectations that may inform both discipline and area of study<br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Canceled	2016-05-26 19:30:28.927918	2016-06-01 00:00:09.584335	Motivate Design	\N	t	\N
