727	5858843	UX Art Director	NEW YORK, NY	<div class="p1">POSITION DESCRIPTION</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Lead UX/UI visual design for the Home & Landing Team, one of 7 small cross-functional VS Digital Platform product teams. Each team&#39;s objective is to drive innovation and performance optimization. Intimately understand the inner workings of the area of focus, competitive space and the customer. Work on a monthly release schedule, utilizing an Agile/Lean UX methodology to identify, develop, and iterate customer-facing enhancements.</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Visual & Functional Enhancements</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Innovate & propose functional solutions to enhance the customer experience</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Understand the enhancement objective so this outcome can inform the thinking toward a solution</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Lead Design Studio exercises to generate ideas collectively</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Design final UI leveraging VS standards and best practices </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Collaborate with development team on technical recommendations </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Navigate the site often to understand the site and uncover areas of opportunity</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Create wireframes as needed</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Usability & Test Support</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Be a key contributor in interview questions, comps & prototypes for usability sessions</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Create layouts, low-fi concepts, motion tests, and/or prototypes for GOOB and/or formal usability sessions</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Explore variations in micro interactions for optimal clarity throughout the experience</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Observe usability sessions & focus on extracting key learns to optimize the experience</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Use best practices for preparing & interpreting usability observations</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Competitive Patterning</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Participate in structured patterning exercises to Identify best-in-class functionality from the competition</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Read reports from sites that aggregate findings based on larger usability sessions</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Continued competitive awareness for product best-in-class.</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Front End Build QA</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Leverage tools efficiently to communicate enhancement specification & capture defects (JIRA, Confluence, etc.)</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Work side-by-side with a Front End Web Development to build and validate all visual/functional enhancements</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Ensure visual & interactive integrity of front-end build </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Validate all UI states have been implemented to specifications & standards</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Presentation Support</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Prepare decks as needed for better communication of a concept</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Partner with various creative leads to organize layouts and deliver for executive presentation</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">QUALIFICATIONS</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Sophisticated sense of visual design/style</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Passionate advocate of for usability & user experience</div>\n\n<div class="p1">UI visual design and interaction design expertise</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Proven ability to translate complex design challenges into clear, customer-friendly experiences </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Working understanding of ecommerce and usability best practices</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Collaborative, inclusive and flexible team member</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Resourceful self-starter who gets things done </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Highly organized with extreme attention to detail</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines in a fast-paced environment</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Positive, constructive approach</div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">EXPERIENCE REQUIRED</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Bachelors Degree (Design / Interactive) or equivalent design experience </div>\n\n<div class="p1">7-10 years Web visual design experience</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Mastery of appropriate tools & technology</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Advanced Photoshop</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Working knowledge of Illustrator </div>\n\n<div class="p1">Understanding of the capabilities and best practices relating to the use of front-end Web technologies, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Proven talent in graphic and interactive design</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Retail/fashion brand or agency experience desired; ecommerce experience ideal</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Experience delivering on business and creative goals through design</div>\n\n<div class="p1">Design for tablet & mobile UI </div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p2"> </div>\n\n<div class="p1">LOCATION/TRAVEL: New York City (with travel to Columbus, OH) - See more at: http://careers.lb.com/jobs/ux-art-director-victorias-secret-direct-new-york-ny-job-new-york-new-york-5236990#sthash.fc90XqxR.dpuf</div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.04257	2016-06-01 00:00:09.679893	Victoria's Secret / Limited Brands	\N	f	\N
