703	5109477	Director of User Experience	Richmond, VA	<div style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; line-height: 1.34em; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(54, 54, 54); text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">DIRECTOR OF USER EXPERIENCE, WEB PROPERTIES</span></strong></div>\n\n<div style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.34em; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; color: rgb(54, 54, 54);"><span style="font-size:12px;">We are honored to represent our client, an emerging presence in the automotive industry, in their search for a Director of User Experience<br />\nIn this role you will be responsible for providing best in class user experiences for the companies web properties that are industry-leading and brand-defining. You will lead, mentor, inspire and develop a team of Interaction Designers, Visual Designers and Front End Developers to translate business strategies into world class online experiences that are grounded in consumer truths. AS the SME and strategic voice of the consumer, you will lead the team to pursue creative methods of gathering and interpreting customer perspectives. You will be part of a cross-functional management team tasked with growing a web team that is progressive, efficient and highly engaged.<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<strong>ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES</strong><br />\n<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Create, articulate and champion the vision and standards for all user experience touch points<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Communicate a clear vision to senior executives and other stakeholders that simplifies complexity and generates excitement<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Gather and interpret stakeholder feedback to shape design solutions that meet both business and consumer needs<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Build strong relationships across the organization<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Represent the web team well across the organization and industry<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Direct user research activities to understand consumer needs, opportunities and pain points and to continually inform an iterative design and discovery process<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Create (and direct the creation of) visual artifacts to articulate, inform and validate ideas (prototypes, wireframes, sketches, journey maps, personas, etc.)<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Lead and facilitate meetings and brainstorming sessions <br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Partner with leaders in Product Management, Strategy and IT to establish and refine leaner, more iterative and collaborative processes across the full product development lifecycle<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Build and coach a team of talented associates to deliver on the vision and standards and to be strong collaborators, facilitators and communicators<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Create clear role expectations and leverage industry standards to move the practices forward<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n• Develop associates to reach their full potential - understand their goals and needs, partner in their development, provide advice, feedback, training and advocacy</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<br />\n<strong style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: sans-serif, Arial, Verdana, 'Trebuchet MS'; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6;"><font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">QUALIFICATIONS</span></font></strong></div>\n\n<div style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;"><font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Passion for technology and design, and the drive to stay on top of industry trends and best practices as exhibited through 10+ years of progressively more </span><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 21.4400005340576px;">responsible</span><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;"> experience, 5+Yrs leading UX teams</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Persuasive communicator - able to explain complex or intangible concepts to stakeholders at all levels</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Solid understanding of user-centered design processes and ability to balance customer needs with business goals in developing solutions</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Experience leading user research and brainstorming and product discovery sessions</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Mastery of UX Design principles and deliverables, including rapid prototyping, site maps, information architecture, user personas, wireframes, flows, etc.</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Ability to perform interface design critiques and supply objective feedback to designers </span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Excellent critical thinking and analysis skills </span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Experience managing, training and mentoring others in UX design methodologies and best practices.</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Experience designing solutions for web, mobile, and tablet applications. Responsive/adaptive design experience a plus.</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Proven success designing world class branded web experiences. E-commerce experience a plus.</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">• Experience with Agile development processes a MUST</span></font><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />\n<strong><font color="#363636" face="Open Sans, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.34em;">Candidates must be able to provide a portfolio or work samples showcasing UX prowess, creativity, and depth of thought coupled with fluency in best practices for Interaction Design, Visual Design and Front End Development</span></font></strong></div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.860273	2016-06-01 00:00:09.540776	CarMax	\N	t	\N
