742	4473433	Senior (UX) Visual Designer	San Francisco Bay Area, CA	<span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><u><strong>Senior (UX) Visual Designer</strong></u></span></span><br />\n <br />\n<em><u>Company</u>:</em><br />\nOur client is an industry-leading provider of data integration software. More than 4,000 enterprises worldwide rely on their products held in traditional enterprise, off-premise and in the cloud.<br />\n <br />\n<em><u>Team</u>:</em><br />\nThe Global User Experience Team is responsible for designing consistent and easy to use user experiences for their products. Individual UX designers focus on specific products, and work closely with the PM, Development and QA teams. Visual Designers support UX designers to ensure that the user experience is visually appealing, brand centric and easy to use.<br />\n<br />\n<em><u>Role</u>:</em><br />\nOur client is currently seeking a talented Senior UX Visual Designer in the Bay Area to join their world-class User Experience (UX) team. In this position, you will be responsible for designing visual solutions for our client’s suite of enterprise products.<br />\n<br />\nThis role supports 2 teams (1 new web app/iPad product, and 1 existing cloud product)<br />\n <br />\nUnder the management of the UX Visual Design Manager, the Senior UX Visual Designer works with individual UX designers to provide visual design solutions for complex user experiences such as forms, wizards, charts, filtering, data displays. As well as create visual design assets, such as icons, graphics, layouts, and data visualizations for their products.<br />\n <br />\n<em><u>Ideal Candidate</u>:</em><br />\nThis position is suited for highly creative visual designer with the following traits:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Understanding of complex user experiences within products and providing creative and innovative solutions.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experienced in writing creative briefs and design specifications as well as using existing visual language guidelines and designing high quality professional visuals.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">The ability to provide visual design options for interaction elements and build matured visual design spec documents which could be followed by the development teams.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Fast learner who can work on and manage projects independently, is a good communicator and is skilled at presenting and articulating their visual design solutions.</li>\n</ul>\n <em><u>Responsibilities</u>:</em><br />\nThe Senior UX Visual Designer’s responsibilities involve but are not limited to: \n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work closely with a global team of UX designers and developers to provide comprehensive visual design solutions for various enterprise products.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Learn and comprehend the products to be able to provide better solutions.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Follow visual design trends and techniques to provide modern and timely visual design solutions.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Icon design and production.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Follow existing corporate branding guidelines and apply and extend those through the products.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Have a creative, positive and collaborative attitude.</li>\n</ul>\n<em><u>Qualifications</u>:</em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A minimum of 8 years’ experience in visual design (need strong web based software products, software or desktop software experience)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor&#39;s degree in Graphic Design, HCI, or a related field. (Master’s preferred)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Demonstrated experience conducting complete visual design projects from start to finish.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to develop multiple visual design options and follow a typical design process.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Communicate visual design guidelines, templates, and standards with UX designers & UX teams.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience working in cross-cultural teams highly desirable.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to travel at least once a year for meetings with development partners in Asia.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with icon design (not logos, icons!).</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with interaction/UI design.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with visual design for tablets and mobile.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with creating visual design guidelines & visual specs.</li>\n</ul>\n<em><u>Highly desired tools</u>:</em>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Fireworks, Illustrator, CS5+</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Office Suite, mainly PowerPoint</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Dreamweaver CS5+ or HTML 5 (a plus, not required)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Any demo/animation software (a plus, not required)</li>\n</ul>\n<br 