746	4800180	Studio Manager role with International Digital Agency	New York, NY	<strong>STUDIO MANAGER - INTERNATIONAL AGENCY</strong><br />\n<br />\nOur Client, a premier international digital consulting firm, is seeking a Studio Manager in their New York or San Francisco office.  You will enjoy the resources of a global firm in a part of the company that operates like an innovative, nimble start-up!<br />\n<br />\nThe role responsible for administering and coordinating the core processes required to maintain operations for a global design team with multiple locations. Working with teams and management across the service lines, the successful candidate will be responsible for  You will driving the day to day resourcing decisions, capacity planning, coordinate team recruitment and on boarding, provisioning of tools and hardware, team cost control and revenue collection, maintain a library of marketing materials, and overall team support and escalation. <br />\n<br />\n<strong>Responsibilities: </strong><br />\n<strong>Pipeline coordination</strong>\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with designers, front-office sales teams, service line leads to coordinate incoming work pipeline, identify resource requirements & constraints. </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with teams to understand where priority decisions need to be made between resources and projects where conflicts arise.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Use internal project management system to understand budgets / resources. Variance analysis to understand why project resource went under / over budget.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Track and understand of all projects in the studio.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Maintain resource management system</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Logistics</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Organize logistics for team events</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Take lead on ad-hoc group initiatives.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Maintain team roster and access lists.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Escalate individual technical issues (GRA, building access, etc.)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Handle software licenses and hardware requests.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Maintain and update portfolio site and marketing assets.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Assist with the delivery of HR and implementation of policies / change etc.</li>\n</ul>\n <strong>Financial Administration</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Assist with chargebacks and validate vendor invoices.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with service line leads and Finance to ensure budgets are being adhered to, creating weekly job analysis and capacity reports to ensure smooth management of run rates across all projects. </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Run weekly freelance report in order to provide transparency on flexible costs. </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Produce monthly capacity report to make sure staff utilization is at optimal levels before engaging additional freelance support.</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\n<b>Requirements</b>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor&#39;s degree</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Minimum of 5 years experience in a multi-office agency or consultancy with direct relevant experiences with project management,  project scoping/burn/P&L, SOWs and resourcing</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong command of English language (both verbal and written)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Passion for design and User Experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Organized, self-motivated and entrepreneurial</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong analytical and problem solving skills paired with the ability to get things done</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Enjoys and gets energized by complex problem solving and ability to push the innovation on solutions</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Excellent communication skills with the ability to influence</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work under pressure, manage expectations effectively and not get overwhelmed by pressures on team</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Distinct customer focus and quality mindset</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to manage own learning and contribute to functional knowledge building</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work both independently and in various team settings</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\n<br />\n <br />\n <br />\n.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.161457	2016-06-01 00:00:09.49322	McKinsey & Company	\N	t	\N
719	5921063	Lead UX Designer	Dallas, Texas	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lead UX Designer</strong></div>\n \n\n<div style="text-align: center;">We are honored to represent our client, a tech company founded in 2008, that is building an innovative, revolutionary wellness platform that will enable individuals to proactively manage their own health and well-being.</div>\n <br />\nThey are looking for a strong UX design leader to work closely with visual designers, product teams, marketing and developers to create the next level of user engagement.  The Lead UX Designer will help construct their strategy for encouraging users to continually take charge of their health through the company’s web and mobile applications. The right person will be passionately curious, adept at innovative approaches to design, masterful at understanding what drives user behavior, and energetic enough to execute rapidly ahead of the competition.<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />\n <br />\n•Guide a team of designers to produce high quality experiences within web and mobile applications<br />\n <br />\n•Formulate a cohesive UX strategy across products and platforms to make usage intuitive, fun, and effortless<br />\n <br />\n•Plan and execute usability studies on a frequent basis to understand our users and test new approaches<br />\n <br />\n•Refine information architecture, interaction design, and visual design with low and high fidelity mockups<br />\n <br />\n•Lead the creation of site maps, concept diagrams, user personas, user scenarios, wireframes, flows, site inventory, template guidelines, and annotated comps, etc.<br />\n <br />\n•Leverage metrics, optimization, qualitative, and quantitative research to inform and validate design decisions<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong><br />\n <br />\n•5+ years of design experience producing engaging, usable, and effective design solutions using user-centric principles<br />\n <br />\n•1+ year experience managing a design team and providing product direction, planning, and guidance<br />\n <br />\n•Ability to think about high-level product vision while considering feature-level detail<br />\n <br />\n•Adept at usability studies; Able to distill user insights to guide direction for the product<br />\n•Native mobile application design<br />\n•Portfolio presentation is expected, including URLs or samples that reflect work – both web and mobile<br />\n•Available for occasional travel<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Pluses</strong><br />\n <br />\n•Experience with gamification, behavioral economics, and analytical dashboards<br />\n•Bachelor and/or Master Degree in a Relevant Field of Study (i.e. Human Computer Interaction, Computer Science, Graphic Design, New Media, Engineering, Liberal Arts, etc.)<br />\n•Experience with one or more prototyping tools: Axure, OmniGraffle, Visio, Balsamiq, Fireworks, Sketch, InVision, Photoshop or Illustrator<br />\n•Experience working in an Agile environment	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.982768	2016-06-01 00:00:09.695717	HealthMine Services, Inc.	\N	t	\N
702	5947313	Director of Interaction and Design	New York, New York	<div style="text-align: center;">Director, Interaction and Web Design</div>\n<br />\n<font color="#222222" face="Arial, Verdana, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: normal;">Our client, a leading aspirational marketplace site specializing in luxury and one-of-a-kind products is adding a Director of Interaction and Web Design to their team.  Leadership of this well-funded company come from tech forward, highly regarded companies such as Gilt, eBay,Google and Twitter.  This position, a strategic part of the Product team, will focus on merchant services, those functions particular to sellers.</span></font><br />\n <br />\nResponsibilities<br />\nAs the Director of our Interaction and Web Design team, you will be leading a talented group of interaction designers, web designers and user research interns.<br />\n \n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">You should also be able to manage projects as well as people.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">As a member of our leadership team, you will partner with various members of our Product Management organization along with other departments to build the most compelling product experiences.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Job Requirements</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Manage and mentor a team of talented interaction designers (including user interface and visual) and user researchers.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Develop design processes that will help the team scale and produce well-considered designs.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Contribute significantly to strategic design initiatives, from defining our style guidelines, mobile design strategy to site architecture for consumer seller facing experiences.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with team to produce our user experience strategy and develop next generation concepts.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Partner with a wide range of stakeholders from concept to creation, including product managers, marketing, user research, developers, and testing.Director of  </li>\n</ul>\nRequirements\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Candidates should possess a passion for great design, a strong aesthetic sensibility, and the ability to design simple solutions to complex problems.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Candidates must be creative problem solvers, innovative designers, and passionate user advocates.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Comfortable in an agile environment of rapid iteration and experimentation,  and prototyping at various levels of fidelity.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Possess strong verbal, written and visual presentation skills with a deep understanding of the value in storytelling.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Have command of various applications related to prototyping and user interface design (Indesign, Photoshop, Illustrator, Omnigraffle, etc).</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Well versed in collaborative design techniques, rapid prototyping, UI design, UI patterns, time-based visual design and information architecture.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Aware of current trends in design patterns, information visualization and current web technologies such as HTML 5, CSS3, Javascript, gestural UI, animation, etc.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">At least 5+ years of experience designing consumer facing web applications</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">1+ years of managing/mentoring junior designers.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Advanced degree in Human Computer Interaction, Design, or other related discipline.</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.85148	2016-06-01 00:00:09.703069	1stDibs	\N	t	\N
744	4843827	DIRECTOR OF USER EXPERIENCE RESEARCH	New York, New York	<div dir="ltr" id="docs-internal-guid-7fb699ec-3dc2-3273-d885-05b9e47ed499" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Director of Digital Consumer Insights (User Experience)</span></span><br class="kix-line-break" />\n </div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">We are honored to assist our client, a noted financial services firm, as they seek a Director of Digital Consumer Insights for their newly formed innovative, internal, insights driven research team. </span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 51, 153); font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">SUMMARY</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"> </div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">The Director of this newly formed team will implement best-in-class quantitative and qualitative UX research techniques that help drive transformational improvements across the enterprise.</span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">The User experience research team works collaboratively with the UX Design, Visual Design, Product Strategy, Channel Strategy, and Market Research teams. You’ll engage business partners to assess research opportunities, determine priorities, and make recommendations that balance strategic and tactical business needs. You will also be responsible for refining team processes, enhancing research methodologies, developing team members, and maintaining research quality by reviewing team work products.</span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">The team operates as internal consultants that manage in-house projects and external vendors. Therefore, the successful candidate will be an expert at translating both strategic and tactical business needs into research requirements, have deep knowledge of UX research methods and have hands-on experience with online research tools, as well as experience managing vendors.</span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">The Director will be responsible for maximizing team productivity, prioritizing projects, and managing the team-wide research pipeline. </span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 51, 153); font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">RESPONSIBILITIES</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9.35pt;text-indent: -9.35pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Translate business needs into research designs that answer specific business questions and generate insights that can drive transformational improvements to the user experience</span></div>\n\n<ul style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; margin-left: -24px; background-color: transparent;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Oversee and prioritize all UX research across all digital platforms</span></div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9.35pt;text-indent: -9.35pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> </span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Identify and implement a variety of methods for getting input and feedback from customers, including lab-based and remote user testing, usability studies, customer co-creation methods, beta testing, site surveys, diary studies, in-depth interviews, online surveys, focus groups (in-person and remote), card-sorting exercises, tree tests, etc.</span></div>\n\n<ul style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; margin-left: -24px; background-color: transparent;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Develop deep engagement and relationships with internal clients & business partners</span></div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9.35pt;text-indent: -9.35pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Integrate website metrics, primary research, and syndicated research to identify best practices and design opportunities</span></div>\n\n<ul style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; margin-left: -24px; background-color: transparent;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Establish and document team processes & operational guidelines</span></div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9.35pt;text-indent: -9.35pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Provide coaching & development for team members</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9.35pt;text-indent: -9.35pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Manage and prioritize a portfolio of blue-chip projects with tight deadlines </span><br class="kix-line-break" />\n </div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 51, 153); font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">REQUIREMENTS</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> 10+ years of experience with custom primary research, both qualitative and quantitative</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> 2+ years of experience in a digital environment and/or researching digital properties. UX research expertise key.</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.0791666666666666;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> 2+ years of experience managing corporate research teams and external vendors</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Strong prioritization, project management, time management, and organizational skills in a fast-paced environment</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Strong written and verbal communication skills, including executive presentation skills</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Calibri; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">●</span><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"> Expertise in designing user experience research, writing interview guides, and conducting user tests</span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-left: 9pt;text-indent: -9pt;"> </div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	On Hold	2016-05-26 19:30:29.149461	2016-06-01 00:00:09.500146	eTrade	\N	t	\N
705	5965652	Senior UX Researcher	New York, New York	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Senior UX Researcher</strong><br />\n<br />\n<em>Work with the best of the best on products used worldwide!</em></div>\n<br />\nOur client, a global financial technology and media company offering a state of the art research lab and a best in class UX design model is adding a <strong>Senior UX Researcher</strong> to their team of innovators who are committed to creating valuable and meaningful user experiences for their customers. You will transform complex data and work processes into products that are indispensable to users.<br />\n <br />\n<strong>They are looking for a Senior UX Researcher with expertise in complex software and business systems.  Your responsibilities will include: </strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Lead qualitative and quantitative user research initiatives that inform critical decisions for current and future Bloomberg products.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work closely with cross-product teams to identify research topics that inform business decisions and use best practices in user research to support the entire product design cycle.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Design and execute exploratory field studies with users and subject-matter experts.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Plan, recruit for, and conduct usability analyses in our state-of-the-art usability lab, in the field, or using remote tools.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Collaborate closely with designers, technologists, and product managers and deliver persuasive and compelling findings to executive stakeholders.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Your background will include the following qualifications:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5+ years of experience in user research and usability analysis.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">The ideal candidate is driven by the desire to be a user advocate and is passionate about gathering insights based on direct observation to create products that are intuitive, satisfying, and easy to learn.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proven track record executing ethnographic and usability studies to evaluate complex workflows across rich software interfaces on desktop, mobile, and the web.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience evaluating platform-level functionality (such as operating system features and user interface toolkits) is a plus.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Superior verbal and written presentation skills to communicate clear, concise findings and actionable recommendations to designers, technologists, project managers, and executives.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proficiency in qualitative and quantitative data analysis, remote testing, eye tracking, testing mobile interfaces, card sorting, survey evaluation, A/B and multivariate testing, and heuristic evaluations.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Working knowledge of data-logging tools such as Ovo Studios, Morae, Camtasia, etc.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with statistical analysis is a plus.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">B.S. in Human-Computer Interaction, Human Factors, Interaction Design, Cognitive Psychology, Cognitive Science, or related field is preferred; M.S. or Ph.D. is highly desired.</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\nPortfolio requested<br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.878945	2016-06-01 00:00:09.712512	Bloomberg	\N	t	\N
698	5910857	Project Management Intern	New York, New York	<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.7999999999999998;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5289fc5b-283c-0d81-f1f9-dad00327f1d5"><span style="font-size: 13.3333333333333px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;">SUMMARY</span></span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.7999999999999998;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5289fc5b-283c-0d81-f1f9-dad00327f1d5"><span style="font-size: 13.3333333333333px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;">Motivate Design is a leading research-driven design and innovation agency in NYC. We work with our partners to create exceptional brand experiences that humanize technology, improve people&#39;s lives and create new value for their businesses. We are looking for an intern to work with the director of operations to manage projects this fall, with the potential to extend the internship into the spring.</span></span></div>\n \n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.7999999999999998;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5289fc5b-283c-0d81-f1f9-dad00327f1d5"><span style="font-size: 13.3333333333333px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;">JOB DESCRIPTION</span></span></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.7999999999999998;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5289fc5b-283c-0d81-f1f9-dad00327f1d5"><span style="font-size: 13.3333333333333px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: transparent;">The intern will assist with project management by taking on responsibilities that support and advance major projects in the office. The intern is expected to b