nts<br />\n·      Consult on UX design deliverables including their fitness for testing<br />\n·      Design and mine usage analytics to identify patterns bearing investigation<br />\n·      Help operate the user experience lab<br />\n·      Mentor junior level employees<br />\n <br />\n <br />\n <br />\n<strong>Qualifications</strong><br />\n <br />\n·      5+ years of related experience designing, developing, implementing and supporting multi-platform Internet and Intranet applications and mechanisms that monitor use, performance and growth.<br />\n·      A Master&#39;s degree, preferably in HCI, or a comparable level of job experience<br />\n·      Knowledge of prototyping tools and technologies are a plus, such as Axure RP, Dreamweaver, Photoshop, Visio, Balsamiq, or CSS/HTML/JavaScript.<br />\n·      Unquestionable interpersonal and communication skills<br />\n·      Experience in evaluating solutions for the financial services industry, especially interfaces for traders, analysts or other front office personnel or customers a plus.<br />\n·      Experience with user research applications is a plus, such as WebSort, Morae, OvoStudios, or screen recording/video editing software<br />\n <br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.300594	2016-06-01 00:00:09.350058	Bank of New York Mellon	\N	t	\N
