758	1831643	Senior User Experience Designer	Hartford, CT	<br />\n<strong>SENIOR USER EXPERIENCE DESIGNER</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe <strong>User Experience Designer </strong>will design creative solutions that promote user adoption, self-service, and ease of use to support the business needs.   This multidiscipline position calls for a technically savvy person that is equal parts: research analyst, information architect, interaction designer, and visual designer. <br />\n<br />\nIn this role you will approach design from a user-perspective and balance users&#39; needs alongside business goals and technical capabilities. You will be working closely with product managers, software developers and web designers to determine necessary features and drive the design of products. The ideal candidate will have experience conducting user research, extracting requirements, designing an interaction framework, iterating on your framework, and presenting your ideas to development and management.<br />\n<br />\nStrategic User Experience Design Expertise and Analytical Skills\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"> Design and Deliver compelling, elegant, pleasurable and sophisticated end-to-end user experience solutions for multiple products and platforms, from assessing and defining customer needs to delivering concepts, to prioritizing features, to presenting and evaluating prototypes, to validating user experience feedback </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work Effectively in Diverse Team Structures </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Research End Users and Competitive Products and Services </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Set User Experience Goals that Balance Business, Technology and End User Needs</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">