le guides<br />\n·         Practical knowledge of user research methods, including lab-based usability studies, field studies, and usability inspections (heuristic evaluations or cognitive walkthroughs),<br />\n·         Excellent analytical ability, especially with regard to observation of user behavior<br />\n·         Proficiency with design and software prototyping tools, including Adobe Creative Suite, Axure, HTML, CSS.<br />\n·         Proficiency with diagramming software such as Visio or Omnigraffle.<br />\n·         Axure Rapid Prototyping knowledge a plus.<br />\n·         Thorough understanding of the web, and it’s associated technologies – their power and limitations<br />\n·         Working knowledge of HTML, XHTML, CSS, JavaScript, and JavaScript - will not be coding<br />\n·         Working knowledge of Web standards development and best practices<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Portfolio</strong><br />\n<br />\n·         A Strong Portfolio demonstrating past work producing elegant user-centered User Experience Design solutions is highly recommended. Please include a link to your portfolio on your resume.<br />\n·         Portfolio should feature sample personas, scenarios, task analyses, task flows, sitemaps, mockups, wireframes, prototypes, functional specifications, style guides, and other assets reflective of a multidiscipline UX designer.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:29.25241	2016-06-01 00:00:10.3661	ESPN	\N	t	\N
