-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Obsession for detail and consistency.</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Mastery in the application of layout, color, and typography.</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Highly skilled in Photoshop, Illustrator, Sketch and/or other design tools.</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Able to distill loads of information into actionable design principles</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Strong problem finding and solving skills</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Highly skilled in prototyping at the appropriate fidelity</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Strong knowledge of technical capabilities and constraints across devices</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Ability to prototype in HTML/CSS is a bonus</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Mobile design experience familiarity with mobile development is a bonus</b></div>\n\t</li>\n\t<li dir="ltr" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">\n\t<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Travel industry and e-commerce experience is a bonus</b><br />\n\t </div>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Portfolio Required</b></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Relocation offered</b></div>\n\n<div dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-dbf65bbc-4dbb-c4cc-2b89-19023056d6c2">Amazing benefits, including free travel</b></div>\n<br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.869397	2016-06-01 00:00:10.785914	Gozengo	\N	t	\N
802	7823978	Product Designer	New York, NY	<div><b>Company Description:</b><br />\nOur client is a 2 year old, well-funded, mission-driven startup in the healthcare space, which is building a state-of-the-art collaborative mental and physical health ecosystem. Their technology platform allows seamless communication and collaboration between medical and behavioral health providers, leading to targeted, timely and higher quality patient care.<br />\n<br />\nUtilizing an advanced data engine, our client works with health plans and health systems to provide actionable population insights that improve patient outcomes and reduce costs.<br />\n </div>\n\n<div><b>Role Overview:</b><br />\nOur client&#39;s product has three platforms and 4 primary stakeholders, which include primary care providers, behavioral therapists, psychiatrists and patients. Some of their products are already live in 2 major cities, and they are currently building out and refining their other platforms.<br />\n<br />\nThis position reports to the Head of Product and you will be working alongside the Visual Designer, who will support the creation of content and assets for the entire user experience. <br />\n<br />\nYou will be responsible for the hands-on process of research, testing, wire-framing, interaction design and prototyping for all products.  As the Product Designer, you will create and improve user-flows and content to increase user engagement and loyalty. You will have full ownership of all user experience across products- from wire-framing through user interface to content.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Team Overview:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Reports to Head of Product</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">2 product managers on provider tool</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">1 product manager on patient tool</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Director of product platforms (back end data side)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Cross functional visual designer</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">2 associate product managers</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">3-4 front-end engineers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div><br />\n<b>Qualifications:</b></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5 + years experience</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong wireframing and prototyping skills</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to research and understand users</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Prior UX/UI experience with web and mobile applications</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Cross platform (horizontal and vertical) experience (Responsive design, native apps)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong communication skills </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Comfort with a fast-paced, iterative environment </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"><b>The Ideal Candidate:</b></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">User-centric design experience - empathy for the user and ability to turn research/understanding into designs that engage users</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Tangible examples of how your UX work translated into engagement (birth of a new user base, use of a new feature or growth of an existing user base, etc).</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Data-driven design with products that already had large user-bases isn&#39;t as good a fit - prefer someone who has done at least one thing early </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">UI/User Flow/UserInteraction design experience - wires into engaging UI </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Someone who considers UX to go beyond the UI - copy, user touchpoints, etc. - everything the user experiences </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience designing a user application that served a utility - the user used the app to do something other than consuming content)</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">B to C experience primary - B to B secondary - both is great </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Mobile/responsive design experience is pretty important </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">The ability to hold a team to a high UX bar - process & personality to ensure that products meet that bar</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Passion for our mission - with a focused understanding that the patient journey is the central focus - and all other users are actors </li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Cultural fit - this ties to their ability to hold the UX bar</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A good fit to work with visual design in a complementary way</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Good startup personality - ability to make difficult decisions in ambiguous situation</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-07-15 20:00:14.149267	2016-09-21 00:00:08.899886	Quartet Health	Startup	t	\N
621	5955521	iOS Interaction Designer	NYC, New York	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>iOS Interaction Designer</strong></div>\n <br />\nOur client, a leading aspirational marketplace site specializing in luxury and one-of-a-kind products is adding a talented iOS Interaction Designer to their team.  Leadership of this well-funded company come from tech forward, highly regarded companies such as Gilt, eBay, Google and Twitter.  <br />\n <br />\nThis position, is a strategic part of the Product Team and will work side by side with senior iOS designers, product managers, developers and the desktop team to create a seamless and intuitive experience for their customers. You should possess a passion for great mobile app design, a strong aesthetic sensibility, and the ability to design simple solutions for complex problems. As a part of our team you will need to thrive in a fast-paced and results-focused environment.<br />\n <br />\n<strong>Requirements</strong>\n\n<div style="margin-left:-6.75pt;">\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">3+ years of experience designing consumer facing iOS applications.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Knowledge of iOS design and web usability principles is a must</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to create wireframes and flows to explore concepts, then transition them to high-fidelity pixel perfect designs</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Possess strong verbal and visual presentation skills, with the ability to articulate the strategy behind your work and why you&#39;ve made certain design decisions.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Partner with a wide range of stakeholders including product managers, marketing, user research, developers, and QA.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience working in a cross-platform environment, mobile and desktop.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Comfortable in an agile environment of rapid iteration and experimentation, prototyping at various levels of fidelity.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.176357	2016-08-02 20:00:10.984941	1stDibs	\N	t	\N
636	4246199	UX Designer	New York, New York	<strong><u>User Experience Designer</u></strong><br />\nNew York City<br />\nLeading Digital Agency<br />\nReports to: Design Leader<br />\n <br />\nOur client is the digital arm of a premier global management consulting firm with 80+ offices in 50 countries. They work with 100 of the top 150 global companies, touching every major industry.<br />\n<br />\nDespite being part of a large, multinational organization, our client works more like a small startup company. Their development teams are small, flexible and employ agile methodologies to quickly provide our consultants with the solutions they need. They combine the latest open source technologies together with traditional Enterprise software products.<br />\n <br />\n<u>What you will be doing</u><br />\nThe experience designer’s primary responsibility will be to drive user experience architecture and design from end-to-end, including wireframes, prototypes, and usability testing;  to create compelling interactive experiences that look great for the intended user segments.Oversee the creative output of your team.<br />\n<br />\n<u>Prerequisites</u>\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Minimum of 1-5 years’ experience in Experience Design</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Knowledge of the agile software development process</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">It is a plus is you have interest in data visualization and can create stunning visuals.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Graphic design skills, including use of a diverse set of software such as Adobe suite, OmniGraffle, Balsamiq, Axure, or other tools for graphic design, visual design.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with conducting user research, usability testing, A/B testing</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Rapid prototyping</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.326253	2016-08-26 16:00:10.371567	McKinsey & Company	In-house	t	\N
668	5379013	UX Design Manager	Coopersburg, PA	<div style="text-align: center;">USER EXPERIENCE DESIGN MANAGER</div>\n <br />\nWe are honored to be representing our client, an innovative hardware and software producer in the Lehigh Valley, in their search for a UX Design Manager.  This is a hands on leadership role in a very collaborative, multidiscipline team.  The company is a leader in their domain and you will have the opportunity to work on a multitude of strategic design initiative and new product development.<br />\n <br />\nRESPONSIBILITES\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Leading stakeholder interview to define business need.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Leading user research to understand user needs and wants.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Review and analyze user research and develop user personas and workflow.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Developing product strategy and prioritize features.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Developing Information architecture and user interface design to exceed user’s expectation and create positive emotion.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Developing digital and paper mock-up/prototypes and testing with users.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Leading a team of designers and work collaboratively to present design and ideas to cross-functional teams including product managers, engineering leaders, stakeholders and senior management.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with highly skilled computer science professionals to deliver world class user experience to the end user.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Mentoring and coaching team members to expand the effectiveness of those around you</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Establish best practices, process improvements, clean designs, and smart testing and review practices.</li>\n</ul>\n QUALIFICATIONS\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor’s degree in Human Computer Interaction(HCI), design, human factors, Engineering Psychology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering with at least a 3.0 GPA (or equivalent).</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5 to 7 years of industry experience in the field of User Interface Design.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Thorough knowledge of human interface design fundamentals and hands-on experience with in design UI prototypes.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to work collaboratively while also thriving in a leadership position.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Hands-on attitude and a strong work ethic.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Communication skills with all departments and disciplines.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Skillful at solving problems with enthusiasm and creativity.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Driven to maintain high standards of quality.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong ability to work and manage across the organization.</li>\n</ul>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.619963	2016-06-01 00:00:10.689989	LUTRON	\N	t	\N
717	6004943	Creative Recruitment Coordinator	New York, NY	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Creative Recruitment Coordinator</strong></div>\n <br />\nUX Hires is a rapidly growing, niche talent staffing firm in FIDI that focuses on UX, UI, and digital product designers. Sitting in the same office as its parent company, Motivate Design, (a premier research and design agency), UX Hires has the unique opportunity to be part of a true design-driven environment, which helps our recruitment team understand their space on a deeper level.<br />\n <br />\nOur philosophy consists of three parts: <br />\n1.     Stay far away from the traditional staffing agency environment (value/reward teamwork)<br />\n2.     Embrace the future of recruitment (social recruitment, recruitment marketing, new technologies)<br />\n3.     Become leaders in our niche space, promote user-centered design thinking, and build stronger UX design practices within out client companies.<br />\n<br />\nOur small team is looking to bring on a creative recruitment coordinator whose role it will be to ensure organization and efficiency across our firm.<br />\n<br />\nYour duties will include the following:<br />\n·       Manage online applicants through our ATS and help route top talent to our recruiters<br />\n·       Screen resumes for quality and handle occasional candidate calls<br />\n·       Manage our social media activity/posts<br />\n·       Helping to construct and post job descriptions<br />\n·       Schedule calls/interviews<br />\n·       Ensuring the input of data into our ATS after recruitment calls<br />\n·       Generating content for inclusion on the website, marketing outreach programs, client updates, candidate newsletters and other outward facing mediums to increase our firm&#39;s exposure<br />\n <br />\nYou should bring:<br />\n·       Some knowledge of the creative space<br />\n·       1+ year of experience as an HR/recruitment coordinator<br />\n·       Experience with social media<br />\n·       Interest in the future of recruitment<br />\n <br />\n <br />\nYou should be hungry, organized, passionate and fun-loving. You have a knack for communication, and eventually relish in the opportunity to manage a small team of interns. We look forward to speaking with you!	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Filled	2016-05-26 19:30:28.967792	2016-06-01 00:00:10.762114	UX Hires	\N	t	\N
