640	7244421	Senior User Experience Designer	Coopersburg, PA	Senior User Experience Designer<br />\n<br />\nJob Description<br />\nWe are honored to represent our client, a domain-leading manufacturer of smart products used world-wide, in their search for a Senior User Experience Designer.  This is an amazing opportunity to work on a variety of innovative hardware and software designs used in residential and commercial environments.<br />\n<br />\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Lead a team of designers and work collaboratively to present designs and ideas to cross-functional teams including product managers, engineering leaders, stakeholders and senior management.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with a cross-functional team to develop product strategy and prioritize features.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Assure a high standard of quality in your own work and in the work of others on your team via best practices, process improvements, clean designs, and smart testing and review practices.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Conduct stakeholder interviews to define business needs.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Conduct user research to understand user needs and wants.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Review and analyze user research and develop user personas and workflow.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Develop Information architecture and user interface designs to exceed users’ expectations and create positive emotions.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Develop digital and paper mock-up/prototypes and testing with users.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with highly skilled