667	6168479	Senior UX Designer	Santa Cruz or San Fransisco, CA	<div style="text-align: center;"> </div>\n\n<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="line-height:normal;width:614px;" width="461">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: center;">\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;"> </div>\n\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;"><strong>SENIOR UX DESIGNER<br />\n\t\t\t<br />\n\t\t\t<em>If you are a senior individual contributor who loves to make things, this is an absolutely wonderful place to work!</em></strong><br />\n\t\t\t </div>\n\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;">We are honored to be representing our client, an emerging presence in business intelligence software, in their search for a Senior UX Designer. The success of their SaaS business intelligence platform products makes it easy for the 250+ industry leading clients to create custom data experiences that access the data in a context that is meaningful to their needs.</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;"><br />\n\t\t\tThey are seeking a Senior User Experience Designer who is dedicated to designing beautiful, useful tools and experiences. You are an experienced and accomplished UX product designer, a self-directed problem solver who is curious, analytical and committed to designing unique and engaging products.</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;"><br />\n\t\t\t </div>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5+ years of user experience design experience for software and/or Web applications that use emergent technologies</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Are familiar with or have some experience with Business Intelligence tools or BI functionality</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to build robust products that are used by thousands or millions of people</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Very high standards. You believe that software is an act of empathy and want to ship the best possible experience to customers</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong conceptualization ability, strong visual communication ability, and wireframing capabilities</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Detailed work flow diagramming capabilities</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Expert working knowledge of Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Omnigraffle</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Are interested in interface design patterns and standard UCD methodologies</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<div style="text-align: left;"><strong>Pluses:</strong></div>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Have experience with HTML, CSS. Extra extra credit for Javascript, SQL, Ruby, and other modern software development languages</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in interaction design, new media design, HCI or related design field</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div><br />\n\t\t\t </div>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.614133	2016-06-01 00:00:11.370786	Looker	Startup	t	UX Design, Product Design
622	5965790	Senior Mobile UX Designer	New York, New York	<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Senior Mobile UX Designer</strong><br />\n<br />\n<em>Work with the best of the best on products used worldwide!</em></div>\n<br />\n <br />\nOur client, a global financial technology and media company offering a state of the art resources and a best in class UX design model is adding a <strong>Senior Mobile UX Designer</strong> to their team of innovators who are committed to creating valuable and meaningful user experiences for their customers. You will transform complex data and work processes into innovative, future forward mobile products that will become indispensable to users.<br />\n <br />\nResponsibilities:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Envision and craft innovative mobile experiences for the all products in their system.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Tackle all aspects of the design process from research to prototyping and presenting to internal clients.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Act as the Mobile SME. Demonstrate mobile expertise and best practices to the broader design, technology and product teams.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Develop concepts from idea through research to final design by leveraging a broad designer toolkit, from sketches, storyboards, user scenarios, personas, wireframes to design prototypes, and detailed wireframe specs for platforms such as iOS, Android Windows Phone and Mobile Web.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Demonstrate deep knowledge of state of the art in user research, user workflow and task modeling, mobile interaction design, information architecture design, conceptual design, best practices in mobile design, design guidelines and heuristics, and ability to evaluate design concepts.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Quickly and effectively communicate your design ideas and rationale</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Present and build confidence around design artifacts such as user research findings, high-level conceptual design ideas, and detailed design specifications.</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\nQualifications:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Undergraduate or Graduate Degree in HCI, Interaction Design, Information Architecture, Visual Communication, or any design-related field.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5+ years of UX design experience.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">3+ years&#39; experience designing native apps for phones and tablets with expertise in platform standards for iOS and Android.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in designing for Blackberry, Windows or Mobile Web is a plus.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in leading design projects.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Highly proficient in design and rapid prototyping tools like Omnigraffle, Visio, InDesign, Illustrator or Photoshop.</li>\n</ul>\n <br />\nA portfolio exemplifying your mobile design skills including sketches, site maps, task flows, wireframes, storyboards and step-by-step user flows is requested.<br />\n <br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Closed	2016-05-26 19:30:28.188918	2016-08-11 20:00:11.859987	Bloomberg	\N	t	\N
809	8009494	Product Design Lead	New York, NY	Like Kleenex® and Coca-Cola®, our client’s brand has become synonymous with the product itself. When CEOs and COOs think of top-notch management consulting, they think of this ubiquitous multinational firm. Our client takes its reputation seriously. But that doesn’t mean they rest on their laurels. They’re constantly thinking of new ways to create digital technologies that transform the way businesses work.<br />\n <br />\nAnd that’s where you come in. If you’ve got over 5 years of experience in mobile and web design (ideally, in an enterprise solutions setting), plus some other nifty attributes, its Innovation group needs a <strong>Product Design Lead</strong>.<br />\n <br />\nAs Product Design Lead reporting to the group’s Director, you’ll….well, <em>take the</em> <em>lead</em> on crafting the UI, developing concepts, prototypes (interaction models, screen designs, and user workflows), wireframes, and mockups that can instantly translate into user stories as well as code.<br />\n <br />\nBut you’ll also contribute to research, ideation & concepting, and product development & delivery—which is why an ability to look at solutions conceptually <em>and </em>pragmatically is so critical. Collaboration is the name of the game here—and you’ll interface regularly with Product Management, Design, Development, Engineering, and Data Analysis. You’ll review and refine design during product development cycles, and provide input on how users would want to interact with an application. You’ll provide expertise on quantitative and qualitative user research: crafting questions, conducting activities, and translating insights. That’s why you need to show you’ve worked with numerous partners before—international partners, too.<br />\n <br />\nUser-centered and iterative design practices—not to mention solid UI skills and expertise with Invision, Adobe suite, OmniGraffle, and Sketch, as well as agile software development practices—are a must. You should want to constantly upgrade those and learn about the newest digital tools and technologies, too.<br />\n <br />\nThough collaboration—as we said—is key, you need to be self-motivating and self-directing on your own tasks, and not shy in reaching out to stakeholders for their input or support. In that sense, be a mentor and a master communicator, clear and concise on why your designs serve the user and the business. There could be some travel—domestic and overseas. Oh, and a sense of humor always helps. But not too much—not everyone loves a joker!	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Active (1)	2016-08-23 00:00:13.92551	2016-08-26 16:00:11.317152	McKinsey & Company	In-house	t	Product Design
