814	8090296	UX Designer	Hoboken, New Jersey	Jet’s mission is to become the smartest way to shop and save on pretty much anything. Combining a revolutionary pricing engine, a world-class technology and fulfillment platform, and incredible customer service, we’ve set out to create a new kind of e-commerce.  At Jet, we’re passionate about empowering people to live and work brilliant.<br />\n<strong>About Jet’s Internal Engine</strong><br />\nWe’re building a new kind of company, and we’re building it from the inside out, which means that investing in hiring, developing, and retaining the brightest minds in the world is a top priority. Everything we do is grounded in three simple values:  trust, transparency, and fairness.  From our business model to our culture, we live our values to the extreme, whether we’re dealing with employees, retail partners, or consumers.  We believe that happiness is the highest level of success and we want every person that crosses paths with Jet to achieve it.  If you’re an ambitious, smart, natural collaborator who likes taking risks, influencing, and innovating in a challenging hyper-growth environment, we’d love to talk to you about joining our team. <br />\n<strong>About the Job</strong><br />\nJet’s Customer Experience Team is in charge of creating a best-in-class shopping experience that allows our customers to embrace all of Jet’s savings opportunities.  As a UX Designer in our prototyping team, you’ll help strategize, define and design frameworks, tools and our internal prototyping platform that facilitates the workflow of our cross-functional product teams. You’ll work alongside a team of passionate product builders who seek to bring the best-in-class experience for our employees and customers.<br />\n <strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Drive the design vision and strategy for Jet’s internal capabilities.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Contribute to defining the design vision and strategy of an end-to-end experience for our in-house prototyping platform.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work cross-functionally with product managers and engineers to build best in class products.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Conduct qualitative and quantitative user research, interviews, usability testing, and other research methods and data analysis techniques.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Create wireframes, flows, prototypes, and designs to effectively communicate interaction and experience.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Conduct interviews with internal stakeholders to identify areas of opportunity for the evolution of the prototyping platform.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Work with product managers and engineers to define and prioritize upcoming features and releases of the prototyping platform.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>About You</strong><br />\n<strong>Must haves:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">5+ years experience as a UX, UI, interaction designer or a similar role</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Deep experience with end-to-end (hybrid UX and UI) product design</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Deep experience partnering with product managers to develop the strategy and design for new features</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience working with diverse teams in a dynamic, rapidly-growing environment</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Fluent in designing for web and native experiences</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with prototyping as a means to explore and communicate design decisions / Front-end development, HTML/CSS, Sketch, Axure, Adobe After Effects or similar</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Strong portfolio demonstrating work user experience, in interaction design, and visual design required</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Bonus points:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience in ecommerce</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Experience with analytical tools</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Compensation Philosophy</strong><br />\nOur compensation philosophy is simple but powerful. Give everyone a meaningful stake in the company—the purest form of ownership. That’s why on top of base salary, Jet’s comp structure is heavily weighted in equity. Our collective hard work, high performance, and tenure are rewarded as our equity builds in value.<br />\n<strong>Benefits & Perks</strong><br />\nCompetitive Salaries.  Unlimited Vacation.  Full Healthcare Benefits.  Exceptional Work Environment.  Learning & Development Opportunities.  Just for fun Networking & Events.<br />\n <br />\n <br />\n 	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Filled	2016-09-06 20:00:14.792737	2016-09-27 20:00:09.37727	Jet.com	In-house	f	UX Design
