827	8709473	Senior Designer (UX/UI)	New York, NY	<section>\n<h2>DESCRIPTION</h2>\n\n<div>We’re looking for an inspirational leader with exceptional knowledge in human-centered and digital design processes to join our Veryday New York team in a full time capacity. In this job you’ll participate in ever-changing projects for our clients worldwide – in industries that range from healthcare and education to finance and consumer electronics. With connected health as the main focus area of our New York office, experience or an interest in healthcare design is a definite plus.</div>\n\n<div>At Veryday, you’ll join a passionate group of individuals that work together to bring an engaged perspective to our three main disciplines: people insight, design impact and business innovation. Our interdisciplinary teams work across UX/CX interaction and design, service design and visual design, and numerous business areas. We offer a highly creative, caring work environment and really love what we do.</div>\n\n<div><strong>What you’ll do as a Design Director at Veryday:</strong></div>\nAs Design Director, you’ll be the visionary owner that interfaces with clients, designers and development teams. You’ll bring a depth of experience and practical expertise in service design and user experience to guide creative and strategic direction on new tasks in both the physical and digital space. In this leadership role, you’ll set methodologies and align client needs with teams curated around envisioned solutions. From beginning to completion of each program, you’ll manage internal teams and ensure that timelines and budgets remain on target. You’ll foster an energetic and supportive atmosphere that raises the bar for all individuals under your direction, and be instrumental in furthering business development and overall organizational goals.</section>\n\n<section>\n<h2>REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n\n<div><strong>Key areas of responsibility for your role will be to:</strong></div>\n\n<div><em>Coordinate 