819	8207622	Product Designer	NYC, NY	<div><strong>Product Designers (Multiple Spots Open!) Wanted for Giant Online Marketplace</strong><br />\n <br />\nLike to get out of your comfort zone?<br />\nJazzed about taking your skills to the next level<br />\nDo you put people first?<br />\n <br />\nWe have a client that puts the “Community” in the phrase “Buying and Selling Community”, and they need multiple <strong>UX Product Designers</strong> (more chances for you!) with over 3 years cross-platform experience to create human-centered experiences for a huge variety of both web-based and native products.<br />\n <br />\nThey’re all about designing tools that are holistic, and everyone who works here loves to dive deep into how users approach every facet of every experience in order to build the style guides and toolkits that make it to market. Right now, the entire organization is super-focused in particular on tackling those very first user touch points and impressions to produce effective and impactful experiences.<br />\n <br />\nThat’s where you come in.<br />\n <br />\nAs a Product Designer, you’re expected to <em>own </em>your users—buyers and sellers alike—and be their UX champion to other internal teams all throughout the product life cycle. You’ll make strategic, people-centered design decisions—underpinned by data and user research—that transform challenging workflows into simple, elegant experiences. Are you a jack-of-all-trades? You’ll thrive! Create detailed interaction flows in the morning, prototypes in the afternoon, and write simple, digestible emails the next day. Collaboration is a way of life here. Fellow designers will have your back, helping you craft cohesive UIs that support the product and the brand. And you’ll also work closely with partners from Product, Engineering, Research, Data, Support, Business, Operations, Brand Design and Marketing, supporting larger goals and strategic thinking.<br />\n <br />\nMake sure you’ve got a great book packed with user-centric UX solutions, high-quality and polished visual design, and solid information architecture. A working knowledge of HTML, SASS/CSS, and other development technologies, plus sketching and prototyping experience—is key. Your colleagues will expect you to trust in the research process. You might be asked to lead research activities! Be open-minded about ideas different than your own, but firm in your own opinions, and confident about communicating them.<br />\n <br />\nWhat might give you an edge? Print and web design know-how (and a clear grasp of pros and cons of both), global marketing campaign experience, and CMS design experience could all help.<br />\n <br />\nFinally, it&#39;s not all computers and colors here. You get to work with people who sing, clog, skateboards, build motorcycles, bike, embroider, emoji, host podcasts, make jewelry, draw comic books, and juggle literal knives. Doesn’t that sound cool?<br />\n </div>\n\n<div> </div>\n\n<div> </div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	On Hold	2016-09-30 00:00:11.257922	2017-01-03 21:00:09.56387	Etsy	In-house	t	Product Design
