820	8222163	Product Designer	Portland, OR	<div>We’re a tech company that’s changing how people bank and think about their finances.</div>\n\n<div>We value empathy, curiosity, craft and efficacy.</div>\n\n<div>Our mission is to help people feel confident with their money.</div>\n\n<div>And we make banking beautiful.</div>\n\n<div><strong>The Job</strong></div>\n\n<div>You will be joining the product design discipline within the Creative Team at Simple. You will work closely with the other members of our team, the Creative Director, the Product Management Team as well as the engineers building our web and mobile apps.</div>\n\n<div>Product Designers at Simple are tasked with taking in and understanding the “who/what/when” of the project and providing the “how”. By knowing the product well, advocating strongly for the customer and understanding the needs of engineers we craft hypotheses and solutions. We stay with an idea from the earliest planning to the shipping of the feature – we’re not only designing the visual experience, but making key decisions about how our product functions to best serve our customers.</div>\n\n<div><strong>The Team</strong></div>\n\n<div>Creative at Simple is a multidisciplinary group of makers, focused on bringing beauty to every aspect of Simple. We help shape the full range of experiences, from the office we work in to the internal and customer-facing products we craft.</div>\n\n<div>In addition to the Creative and Product Design teams, you will have opportunities to work on Simple’s feature teams – small, cross-discipline groups of people with a well defined mission.</div>\n\n<div><strong>You</strong></div>\n\n<div>You are a passionate user and designer of modern applications. You stay up-to-date with the latest design best practices on various platforms (a focus on web or mobile is a-ok). You have opinions about product design, yet keep an open mind and rely heavily on discussions with your peers. We aim to hire empathetic, curious individuals who feel empowered by our company’s mission.</div>\n\n<div>While we do work primarily in the digital, a wide range of interests (e.g. printmaking, photography, music) is a plus. We love producing real world artifacts like our card packaging and customer postcards, and hope you can share in that passion.</div>\n\n<div><strong>Responsibilities</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Design our product with the customer in mind.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Craft the full experience for a variety of features and initiatives on web and/or mobile platforms.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Continuously work to enhance the features and design of our applications.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Partner strongly with the engineers to understand their needs and how they influence the design.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Be an advocate for design within the company.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div><strong>Requirements</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Mobile app design experience for iOS and Android platforms.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to design products to be functional, elegant and easy to use.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Expertise with one or many of: Photoshop, Illustrator, Sketch.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ability to design for a variety of screen sizes, device types and pixel densities.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A well-defined and organized design workflow in whichever software tools you use. Solid use of patterns/widgets within the workflow.</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">A portfolio that shows off your recent digital product design work. Seeing a range of sketches, comps and final designs is a big plus.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div><strong>Details</strong></div>\n\n<div>Simple is based in Portland, OR and we offer a competitive salary and benefits.</div>\n\n<div>Relocation assistance is available. We encourage and subsidize conference participation and continuing education. We believe in work/life balance and fostering a happy workplace.</div>\n\n<div>For more information on Simple, you can start here: https://www.simple.com/about-us/. Our iOS application can be found here: https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/simple-better-banking/id479317486?mt=8.</div>\n\n<div>Note that applications without a cover letter will not be considered.</div>\n\n<div>In compliance with federal law, all persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and to complete the required employment eligibility verification document form upon hire.</div>\n\n<div>Email our team at careers@simple.com if you need an accommodation in the application process.</div>\n\n<div>Simple provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability,​ or genetics. In addition to federal law requirements, ​Simple ​complies with all ​applicable state and local laws governing nondiscrimination in employment in every location in which the company has ​employees. This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training.</div>\n\n<div>By submitting this application, you certify that the facts contained in your application are true and complete to the best of your knowledge.  If you are employed, false statements on your application will be grounds for termination.</div>	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	Canceled	2016-10-04 00:00:10.425069	2016-10-31 20:00:10.0277	Simple	In-house	f	Product Design
832	8838020	Senior Product Designer	New York City, New York	<div style="text-align: center;">SENIOR PRODUCT DESIGNER</div>\n<br />\nJoin a team of start-up stars and financial experts to built products that speak to customer demand!<br />\n<br />\nIt is our pleasure to represent our client, an established and well-funded start-up building a consumer-facing fintech product, in their search for a Lead Product Designer.<br />\n<br />\nAs a core member of the Product Team, you will be instrumental in crafting next-gen financial services products that align the best practices of both technology and user experience. You will act as the UX SME and influence design thinking across the organization.<br />\n<br />\nYour responsibilities will include:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Ownership of design functions at every stage of product development</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Customer research that leads to new/ improved product features</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Creation of user flows, product specifications, wireframes and prototypes</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Oversee usability testing and develop usability standards</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Help develop the look and feel, brand and design specs, for the company and their products</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nYour qualifications should include:\n<ul>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;"> 3+ years of Product Design</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Proven mastery of information architecture, user journeys, interactive models and schematics</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">Visual design for both products and associated collateral, including typography</li>\n\t<li style="padding: 0; margin: 0;" 